INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,   1, 'So let a man think of us as the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s servants, and stewards of God\'s mysteries.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,   2, 'Here, moreover, it is required of stewards that they be found faithful.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,   5, 'So judge nothing before the time, until the Lord<G2962> comes, who will both bring to light the hidden things of darkness, and reveal the counsels of the hearts. Then each man will get his praise from God.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,   9, 'For I think that God has displayed us, the apostles, last of all, like men sentenced to death. For we are made a spectacle to the world, both to angels and men.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,  10, 'We are fools for the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s sake, but you are wise in the AnointedOne<G5547>. We are weak, but you are strong. You have honor, but we have dishonor.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,  14, 'I don\'t write these things to shame you, but to admonish you as my dear<G0027> children.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,  15, 'For though you have ten thousand tutors in the AnointedOne<G5547>, you don\'t have many fathers. For in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus, I became your father through the Good News.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,  16, 'So, I beg you, be imitators of me.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,  17, 'Because of this I have sent Timothy to you, who is my dear<G0027> and faithful child in the Lord<G2962>, who will remind you of my ways which are in the AnointedOne<G5547>, even as I teach everywhere in every assembly.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,  20, 'For God\'s Kingdom is not in word, but in power.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   4,  21, 'What do you want? Shall I come to you with a rod, or in love<G0026> and a spirit of gentleness?');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   5,   2, 'You are proud! Why didn\'t you rather mourn, that he who had done this deed might be removed from among you?');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   5,   7, 'Purge out the old yeast, that you may be a new lump, even as you are unleavened. For indeed the AnointedOne<G5547>, our Passover, has been sacrificed in our place.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   5,   8, 'So let\'s keep the feast, not with old yeast, neither with the yeast of malice and wickedness, but with the unleavened bread of sincerity and truth.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   5,  10, 'yet not at all meaning with the sexual sinners of this world, or with the covetous and extortionists, or with idolaters; for then you would have to leave the world.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   5,  11, 'But as it is, I wrote to you not to associate with anyone who is called a brother who is a sexual sinner, or covetous, or an idolater, or a slanderer, or a drunkard, or an extortionist. Don\'t even eat with such a person.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   5,  12, 'For what do I have to do with judging outsiders? Don\'t you judge those who are within?');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,   4, 'If then you have to judge things pertaining to this life, do you set them to judge who are of no account in the assembly?');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,   7, 'So there is already altogether a defect in you, that you have lawsuits with one another! Why not rather be wronged? Why not rather be defrauded?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,   8, 'No, but you yourselves do wrong and defraud, and that against your brothers.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,   9, 'Or don\'t you know that the unrighteous will not inherit God\'s Kingdom? Don\'t be deceived. Neither the sexually immoral, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor male prostitutes, nor homosexuals,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,  10, 'nor thieves, nor covetous, nor drunkards, nor slanderers, nor extortionists will inherit God\'s Kingdom.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,  11, 'Such were you, but you were washed; but you were sanctified; but you were justified in the name of the Lord<G2962> Jesus, and in the Spirit of our God!');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,  15, 'Don\'t you know that your bodies are members of the AnointedOne<G5547>? Shall I then take the members of the AnointedOne<G5547> and make them members of a prostitute? May it never be!');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,  16, 'Or don\'t you know that he who is joined to a prostitute is one body? For, \"The two\", he says, \"will become one flesh.\"');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,  19, 'Or don\'t you know that your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit who is in you, whom you have from God? You are not your own,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   6,  20, 'for you were bought with a price. So glorify God in your body and in your spirit, which are God\'s.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   7,   3, 'Let the husband give to his wife the affection owed her, and likewise also the wife to her husband.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   7,  10, 'But to the married I command (not I, but the Lord<G2962>) that the wife not leave her husband');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   7,  12, 'But to the rest I (not the Lord<G2962>) say, if any brother has an unbelieving wife, and she is content to live with him, let him not leave her.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   7,  22, 'For he who was called in the Lord<G2962> being a bondservant is the Lord<G2962>\'s free man. Likewise he who was called being free is the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s bondservant.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   7,  26, 'So I think that, because of the distress that is on us, it\'s good for a man to remain as he is.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   7,  34, 'There is also a difference between a wife and a virgin. The unmarried woman cares about the things of the Lord<G2962>, that she may be holy both in body and in spirit. But she who is married cares about the things of the world- how she may please her husband.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   7,  37, 'But he who stands steadfast in his heart, having no necessity, but has power over his own will, and has determined in his own heart to keep his own virgin, does well.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   8,   1, 'Now concerning things sacrificed to idols: We know that we all have knowledge. Knowledge puffs up, but love<G0026> builds up.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   8,   3, 'But if anyone loves<G0025> God is known by him.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   8,   4, 'So concerning the eating of things sacrificed to idols, we know that no idol is anything in the world, and that there is no other God but one.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   8,   5, 'For though there are things that are called \"gods,\" whether in the heavens or on earth; as there are many \"gods\" and many \"lord<G2962>s;\"');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   8,  11, 'And through your knowledge, he who is weak perishes, the brother for whose sake the AnointedOne<G5547> died.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   8,  12, 'Thus, sinning against the brothers, and wounding their conscience when it is weak, you sin against the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   8,  13, 'So, if food causes my brother to stumble, I will not eat meat for evermore, so that I don\'t cause my brother to stumble.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   9,   3, 'My defense to those who examine me is this:');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   9,  12, 'If others partake of this right over you, don\'t we yet more? Nevertheless we didn\'t use this right, but we bear all things, that we may cause no hindrance to the Good News of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   9,  16, 'For if I preach the Good News, I have nothing to boast about; for necessity is laid on me; but woe to me if I don\'t preach the Good News!');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   9,  18, 'What then is my reward? That when I preach the Good News, I may present the Good News of the AnointedOne<G5547> without charge, so as not to abuse my authority in the Good News.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   9,  21, 'to those who are without law, as without law (not being without law toward God, but under law toward the AnointedOne<G5547>), that I might win those who are without law.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   9,  25, 'Every man who strives in the games exercises self-control in all things. Now they do it to receive a temporary<G5349> crown, but we- a permanent<G0862> one.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',   9,  26, 'So I run like that, not aimlessly. I fight like that, not beating the air,');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,   4, 'and all drank the same spiritual drink. For they drank of a spiritual rock that followed them, and the rock was the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,   7, 'Don\'t be idolaters, as some of them were. As it is written, \"The people sat down to eat and drink, and rose up to play.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,   8, 'Let\'s not commit sexual immorality, as some of them committed, and in one day twenty-three thousand fell.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,   9, 'Let\'s not test the Lord<G2962>, as some of them tested, and perished by the serpents.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,  10, 'Don\'t grumble, as some of them also grumbled, and perished by the destroyer.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,  12, 'So let him who thinks he stands be careful that he doesn\'t fall.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,  14, 'So, my dear-ones<G0027>, flee from idolatry.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,  16, 'The cup of blessing which we bless, isn\'t it a sharing of the blood of the AnointedOne<G5547>? The bread which we break, isn\'t it a sharing of the body of the AnointedOne<G5547>?');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,  21, 'You can\'t both drink the cup of the Lord<G2962> and the cup of demons. You can\'t both partake of the table of the Lord<G2962> and of the table of demons.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,  28, 'But if anyone says to you, \"This was offered to idols,\" don\'t eat it for the sake of the one who told you, and for the sake of conscience. For \"the earth is the Lord<G2962>\'s, with all its fullness.\"');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,  30, 'If I partake with thankfulness, why am I denounced for something I give thanks for?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,  31, 'So whether you eat, or drink, or whatever you do, do all to the glory of God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  10,  32, 'Give no occasion for stumbling, whether to Jews, or to Greeks, or to the assembly of God;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,   1, 'Be imitators of me, even as I also am of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,   3, 'But I would have you know that the head of every man is the AnointedOne<G5547>, and the head of the woman is man, and the head of the AnointedOne<G5547> is God.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,   5, 'But every woman praying or prophesying with her head uncovered dishonors her head. For it is one and the same thing as if she were shaved.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,   6, 'For if a woman is not covered, let her hair also be cut off. But if it is shameful for a woman to have her hair cut off or be shaved, let her be covered.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,   9, 'for man wasn\'t created for the woman, but woman for the man.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,  10, 'So the woman ought to have authority on her head, because of the angels.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,  20, 'So when you assemble yourselves together, it is not the Lord<G2960>\'s supper that you eat.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,  22, 'What, don\'t you have houses to eat and to drink in? Or do you despise God\'s assembly and put them to shame who don\'t have enough? What shall I tell you? Shall I praise you? In this I do not praise you.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,  24, 'When he had given thanks, he broke it and said, \"Take, eat. This is my body, which is broken for you. Do this in memory of me.\"');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,  27, 'So whoever eats this bread or drinks the Lord<G2962>\'s cup in a way unworthy of the Lord<G2962> will be guilty of the body and the blood of the Lord<G2962>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,  29, 'For he who eats and drinks in an unworthy way eats and drinks judgment to himself if he doesn\'t discern the Lord<G2962>\'s body.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  11,  33, 'So, my brothers, when you come together to eat, wait for one another.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  12,   3, 'So I make known to you that no man speaking by God\'s Spirit says, \"Jesus is accursed.\" No one can say, \"Jesus is Lord<G2962>,\" but by the Holy Spirit.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  12,   6, 'There are various kinds of workings, but the same God, who works all things in all.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  12,  11, 'But the one and the same Spirit produces all of these, distributing to each one separately as he desires.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  12,  12, 'For as the body is one, and has many members, and all the members of the body, being many, are one body; so also is the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  12,  26, 'When one member suffers, all the members suffer with it. When one member is honored, all the members rejoice with it.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  12,  27, 'Now you are the body of the AnointedOne<G5547>, and members individually.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  13,   1, 'If I speak with the languages of men and of angels, but don\'t have love<G0026>, I have become sounding brass, or a clanging cymbal.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  13,   2, 'If I have the gift of prophecy, and know all mysteries and all knowledge; and if I have all faith, so as to remove mountains, but don\'t have love<G0026>, I am nothing.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  13,   3, 'If I give away all my goods to feed the poor, and if I give my body to be burned, but don\'t have love<G0026>, it profits me nothing.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  13,   4, 'Love<G0026> is patient and is kind. Love<G0026> doesn\'t envy. Love<G0026> doesn\'t brag and isn\'t proud,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  13,   8, 'Love<G0026> never fails. But where there are prophecies, they will be done away with. Where there are various languages, they will cease. Where there is knowledge, it will be done away with.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  13,   9, 'For we know in part and we prophesy in part;');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  13,  13, 'But now faith, hope, and love<G0026> remain- these three. The greatest of these is love<G0026>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,   1, 'Follow after love<G0026> and earnestly desire spiritual gifts, but especially that you may prophesy.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,   9, 'Unless you utter by the tongue words that are easy to understand, how would it be known what is spoken? For you would be speaking into the air.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  11, 'If then I don\'t know the meaning of the sound, I would be a foreigner to him who speaks, and he who speaks would be a foreigner to me.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  13, 'So let him who speaks in another language pray that he may interpret.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  21, 'In the law it is written, \"By men of strange languages and by the lips of strangers I will speak to this people. They won\'t even hear me that way, says the Lord<G2962>.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  22, 'So other languages are for a sign, not to those who believe, but to the unbelieving; but prophesying is for a sign, not to the unbelieving, but to those who believe.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  23, 'So if the whole assembly is assembled together and all speak with other languages, and unlearned or unbelieving people come in, won\'t they say that you are crazy?');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  26, 'What is it then, brothers? When you come together, each one of you has a psalm, has a teaching, has a revelation, has another language, or has an interpretation. Let all things be done to build each other up.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  33, 'for God is not a God of confusion, but of peace, as in all the assemblies of the saints.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  34, 'Let the wives be quiet in the assemblies, for it has not been permitted for them to be talking except in submission, as the law also says,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  35, 'if they desire to learn anything. \"Let them ask their own husbands at home, for it is shameful for a wife to be talking in the assembly.\"');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  37, 'If any man thinks himself to be a prophet or spiritual, let him recognize the things which I write to you, that they are the commandment of the Lord<G2962>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  14,  39, 'So, my brothers, desire earnestly to prophesy, and don\'t forbid speaking with other languages.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,   2, 'by which also you are saved, if you hold firmly the word which I preached to you- unless you believed in vain.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,   3, 'For I delivered to you first of all that which I also received: that the AnointedOne<G5547> died for our sins according to the Scriptures,');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  10, 'But by the grace of God I am what I am. His grace which was given to me was not futile, but I worked more than all of them; yet not I, but the grace of God which was with me.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  12, 'Now if the AnointedOne<G5547> is preached, that he has been raised from the dead, how do some among you say that there is no resurrection of the dead?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  13, 'But if there is no resurrection of the dead, neither has the AnointedOne<G5547> been raised.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  14, 'If the AnointedOne<G5547> has not been raised, then our preaching is empty, and your faith also is empty.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  15, 'So, we are then false witnesses of God, because we testified about God that he raised up the AnointedOne<G5547>. He didn\'t raise him up if the dead aren\'t ever raised.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  16, 'For if the dead aren\'t raised, neither has the AnointedOne<G5547> been raised.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  17, 'If the AnointedOne<G5547> has not been raised, your faith is useless; you are still in your sins.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  18, 'Then they also who are fallen asleep in the AnointedOne<G5547> have perished.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  19, 'If we have only hoped in the AnointedOne<G5547> in this life, we are of all men most pitiable.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  20, 'But now the AnointedOne<G5547> has been raised from the dead. He became the first fruits of those who are asleep.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  22, 'For as in Adam all die, so also in the AnointedOne<G5547> all will be made alive.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  23, 'But each in his own order: the AnointedOne<G5547> the first fruits, then those who are the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s, at his coming.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  24, 'Then the end comes, when he will deliver up the Kingdom to God, even the Father, when he will have abolished all rule and all authority and power.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  27, 'For, \"He put all things in subjection under his feet.\" But when he says, \"All things are put in subjection\", it is evident that he is excepted who subjected all things to him.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  32, 'If I fought with animals at Ephesus for human purposes, what does it profit me? If the dead are not raised, then \"let\'s eat and drink, for tomorrow we die.\"');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  38, 'But God gives it a body even as it pleased him, and to each seed a body of its own.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  40, 'There are also celestial bodies and terrestrial bodies; but the glory of the celestial differs from that of the terrestrial.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  42, 'So also is the resurrection of the dead. The body is sown perishable; it is raised imperishable.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  50, 'Now I say this, brothers, that flesh and blood can\'t inherit God\'s Kingdom; neither does corruption inherit incorruption.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  52, 'in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet will sound and the dead will be raised permanent<G0862>, and we will be changed.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  53, 'For this temporary<G5349> must be clothed in permanency, and this mortal must put on immortality.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  54, 'But this temporary<G5349> will have put on permanency, and this mortal will have put on immortality, then what is written will happen: \"Death is swallowed up in victory.\"');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  15,  58, 'So, my dear<G0027> brothers, be steadfast, immovable, always abounding in the Lord<G2962>\'s work, because you know that your labor is not in vain in the Lord<G2962>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  16,   2, 'On the first day of every week, let each one of you save, as he may prosper, that no collections are made when I come.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  16,  11, 'So let no one despise him. But set him forward on his journey in peace, that he may come to me; for I expect him with the brothers.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  16,  14, 'Let all that you do be done in love<G0026>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  16,  15, 'Now I beg you, brothers- you know the house of Stephanas, that it is the first fruits of Achaia, and that they have set themselves to serve the saints-');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  16,  18, 'For they refreshed my spirit and yours; so acknowledge those who are like that.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  16,  22, 'If any man doesn\'t love the Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, let him be accursed. Maranatha!');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1CO',  16,  24, 'My love<G0026> to all of you in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus. Amen.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   1,   5, 'For as the sufferings of the AnointedOne<G5547> abound to us, even so our comfort also abounds through the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   1,   7, 'Our hope for you is steadfast, knowing that, since you are partakers of the sufferings, you also are of the comfort.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   1,  11, 'you also helping together on our behalf by your supplication; that, for the gift given to us by means of many, thanks may be given by many persons on your behalf.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   1,  13, 'For we write no other things to you than what you read or even acknowledge, and I hope you will acknowledge to the end,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   1,  15, 'In this confidence, I was determined to come first to you, that you might have a second benefit,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   1,  17, 'So when I was determined in that way, did I show fickleness? Or the things that I purpose, do I purpose according to the flesh, so that with me there should be the \"Yes, yes\" with the \"No, no\"?');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   1,  20, 'For however many are the promises of God, in him is the \"Yes.\" Therefore also through him is the \"Amen\", to the glory of God through us.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   1,  21, 'Now he who establishes us with you in the AnointedOne<G5547> and anointed us is God,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   1,  24, 'Not that we dominate<G2961> your faith, but are fellow workers with you for your joy. For you stand firm in faith.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,   2, 'For if I make you grieve, then who will make me glad but he who is made to grieve by me?');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,   4, 'For out of much affliction and anguish of heart I wrote to you with many tears, not that you should be made to grieve, but that you might know the love<G0026> that I have so abundantly for you.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,   6, 'This punishment which was inflicted by the many is sufficient for such a one;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,   8, 'So I beg you to confirm your love<G0026> toward him.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,  10, 'Now I also forgive whomever you forgive anything. For if indeed I have forgiven anything, I have forgiven that one for your sakes in the presence of the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,  11, 'that no advantage may be gained over us by Satan, for we are not ignorant of his schemes.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,  12, 'Now when I came to Troas for the Good News of the AnointedOne<G5547>, and when a door was opened to me in the Lord<G2962>,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,  14, 'Now thanks be to God, who always leads us in triumph in the AnointedOne<G5547>, and reveals through us the sweet aroma of his knowledge in every place.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,  15, 'For we are a sweet aroma of the AnointedOne<G5547> to God, in those who are saved and in those who perish:');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,  16, 'to the one a stench from death to death, to the other a sweet aroma from life to life. Who is sufficient for these things?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   2,  17, 'For we are not as so many, peddling the word of God. But as of sincerity, but as of God, in the sight of God, we speak in the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,   2, 'You are our letter, written in our hearts, known and read by all men,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,   3, 'being revealed that you are a letter of the AnointedOne<G5547>, served by us, written not with ink, but with the Spirit of the living God; not in tablets of stone, but in tablets that are hearts of flesh.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,   4, 'Such confidence we have through the AnointedOne<G5547> toward God,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,   5, 'not that we are sufficient of ourselves, to account anything as from ourselves; but our sufficiency is from God,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,   6, 'who also made us sufficient as servants of a new covenant, not of the letter, but of the Spirit. For the letter kills, but the Spirit gives life.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,   7, 'But if the service of death, written engraved on stones, came with glory, so that the children of Israel could not look steadfastly on the face of Moses for the glory of his face, which was passing away,');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,  12, 'So having such a hope, we use great boldness of speech,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,  14, 'But their minds were hardened, for until this very day at the reading of the old covenant the same veil remains, because in the AnointedOne<G5547> it passes away.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,  16, 'But whenever someone turns to the Lord<G2962>, the veil is taken away.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   3,  18, 'But we all, with unveiled face seeing the glory of the Lord<G2962> as in a mirror, are transformed into the same image from glory to glory, even as from the Lord<G2962>, the Spirit.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,   1, 'So seeing we have this ministry, even as we obtained mercy, we don\'t faint.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,   2, 'But we have renounced the hidden things of shame, not walking in craftiness, nor handling the word of God deceitfully, but by the manifestation of the truth commending ourselves to every man\'s conscience in the sight of God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,   3, 'Even if our Good News is veiled, it is veiled among those who perish;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,   4, 'in whom the god of this world has blinded the minds of the unbelieving, that the light of the Good News of the glory of the AnointedOne<G5547>, who is the image of God, should not dawn on them.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,   5, 'For we don\'t preach ourselves, but AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus as Lord<G2962>, and ourselves as your servants for Jesus\' sake,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,   6, 'seeing it is God who said, \"Light will shine out of darkness,\" who has shone in our hearts to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,   9, 'pursued, yet not forsaken<G1459>; struck down, yet not destroyed;');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,  12, 'So then death works in us, but life in you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,  13, 'But having the same spirit of faith, according to that which is written, \"I believed, and therefore I spoke.\" We also believe, and therefore we also speak;');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,  16, 'So we don\'t faint, but though our outward person is decaying, yet our inward person is renewed day by day.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   4,  17, 'For our light affliction, which is for the moment, works for us more and more exceedingly an eternal weight of glory,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,   2, 'For most certainly in this we groan, longing to be clothed with our habitation which is from heaven,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,   3, 'if indeed being clothed, we will not be found naked.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,   4, 'For indeed we who are in this tent do groan, being burdened, not that we desire to be unclothed, but that we desire to be clothed, that what is mortal may be swallowed up by life.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,   6, 'So we are always confident and know that while we are at home in the body, we are absent from the Lord<G2962>;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,   8, 'We are courageous, I say, and are willing rather to be absent from the body and to be at home with the Lord<G2962>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,   9, 'So we also make it our aim, whether at home or absent, to be well pleasing to him.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,  10, 'For we must all be revealed before the judgment seat of the AnointedOne<G5547> that each one may receive the things in the body according to what he has done, whether good or bad.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,  11, 'So, knowing the fear of the Lord<G2962>, we persuade men, but we are revealed to God, and I hope that we are revealed also in your consciences.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,  14, 'For the love<G0026> of the AnointedOne<G5547> constrains us; because we judge thus, that one died for all, therefore all died.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,  16, 'So from now on we know no one according to the flesh. Even though we have known the AnointedOne<G5547> according to the flesh, now we no longer know him in that way.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,  17, 'So if anyone is in the AnointedOne<G5547>, he is a new creation. The old things have passed away. Behold, all things have become new.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,  19, 'namely, that God was in the AnointedOne<G5547> reconciling the world to himself, not reckoning to them their trespasses, and having committed to us the word of reconciliation.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   5,  20, 'So we are ambassadors on behalf of the AnointedOne<G5547>, as though God were entreating by us: we beg you on behalf of the AnointedOne<G5547>, be reconciled to God.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   6,   1, 'Working together, we urge you also not to receive the grace of God in vain,');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   6,   6, 'in pureness, in knowledge, in perseverance, in kindness, in the Holy Spirit, in sincere love<G0026>,');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   6,  13, 'Now in return, I speak as to my children: you also widen your hearts.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   6,  14, 'Don\'t be unequally yoked with unbelievers, for what fellowship do righteousness and iniquity have? Or what fellowship does light have with darkness?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   6,  15, 'What agreement does the AnointedOne<G5547> have with Belial? Or what portion does a believer have with an unbeliever?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   6,  16, 'What agreement does a temple of God have with idols? For you are a temple of the living God. Even as God said, \"I will dwell in them and walk in them. I will be their God and they will be my people.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   6,  17, 'So \"\'Come out from among them, and be separate,\' says the Lord<G2962>. \'Touch no unclean thing. I will receive you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   6,  18, 'I will be to you a Father. You will be to me sons and daughters,\' says the Lord<G2962> Almighty<G3841>.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   7,   1, 'So, having these promises, dear-ones<G0027>, let us cleanse ourselves from all defilement of flesh and spirit, perfecting holiness in the fear of God.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   7,   3, 'I say this not to condemn you, for I have said before that you are in our hearts to die together and live together.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   7,   6, 'Nevertheless, he who comforts the lowly, God, comforted us by the coming of Titus,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   7,   7, 'and not by his coming only, but also by the comfort with which he was comforted in you while he told us of your longing, your mourning, and your zeal for me, so that I rejoiced still more.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   7,   8, 'For though I grieved you with my letter, I do not regret it, though I did regret it. For I see that my letter made you grieve, though just for a while.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   7,   9, 'I now rejoice, not that you were grieved, but that you were grieved to repentance. For you were grieved in a godly way, that you might suffer loss by us in nothing.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   7,  10, 'For godly sorrow produces repentance to salvation, which brings no regret. But the sorrow of the world produces death.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   7,  11, 'For behold, this same thing, that you were grieved in a godly way, what earnest care it worked in you. Yes, what defense, indignation, fear, longing, zeal, and vengeance! In everything you demonstrated yourselves to be pure in the matter.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   7,  13, 'So we have been comforted. In our comfort we rejoiced the more exceedingly for the joy of Titus, because his spirit has been refreshed by you all.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,   1, 'Moreover, brothers, we make known to you the grace of God which has been given in the assemblies of Macedonia,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,   2, 'how in much proof of affliction, the abundance of their joy and their deep poverty abounded to the riches of their generosity.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,   5, 'This was not as we had expected, but first they gave their own selves to the Lord<G2962>, and to us through the will of God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,   6, 'So we urged Titus, that as he had made a beginning before, so he would also complete in you this grace.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,   7, 'But as you abound in everything, in faith, utterance, knowledge, all earnestness, and in your love<G0026> to us, see that you also abound in this grace.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,   8, 'I speak not by way of commandment, but as proving through the earnestness of others the sincerity also of your love<G0026>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,   9, 'For you know the grace of our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, that though he was rich, yet for your sakes he became poor, that you through his poverty might become rich.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,  10, 'I give a judgment in this: for this is expedient for you who were the first to start a year ago, not only to do, but also to be willing.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,  18, 'We have sent together with him the brother whose praise in the Good News is known throughout all the assemblies.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,  19, 'Not only so, but he was also appointed by the assemblies to travel with us in this grace, which is served by us to the glory of the Lord<G2962> himself, and to show our readiness.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,  23, 'As for Titus, he is my partner and fellow worker for you. As for our brothers, they are the apostles of the assemblies, the glory of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   8,  24, 'So show the proof of your love<G0026> to them in front of the assemblies, and of our boasting on your behalf.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   9,   2, 'for I know your readiness, of which I boast on your behalf to the of Macedonians, that Achaia has been prepared for the past year. Your zeal has stirred up very many of them.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   9,   4, 'so that if any Macedonians come with me and find you unprepared, we (to say nothing of you) would be disappointed in this confident boasting.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   9,   5, 'So I thought it necessary to entreat the brothers that they would go before to you and arrange ahead of time the generous gift that you promised before, that the same might be ready as a matter of generosity, and not of greediness.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   9,   7, 'Let each man give according as he has determined in his heart, not grudgingly or under compulsion, for God loves<G0025> a cheerful giver.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   9,   9, 'As it is written, \"He has scattered abroad. He has given to the poor. His righteousness remains forever.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   9,  10, 'Now may he who supplies seed to the sower and bread for food, supply and multiply your seed for sowing, and increase the fruits of your righteousness,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   9,  11, 'you being enriched in everything to all generosity, which produces thanksgiving to God through us.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   9,  12, 'For this service of giving that you perform not only makes up for lack among the saints, but abounds also through much giving of thanks to God,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',   9,  13, 'seeing that through the proof given by this service, they glorify God for the obedience of your confession to the Good News of the AnointedOne<G5547> and for the liberality of your contribution to them and to all,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  10,   1, 'Now I Paul, myself, entreat you by the humility and gentleness of the AnointedOne<G5547>, I who in your presence am lowly among you, but being absent am bold toward you.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  10,   5, 'throwing down imaginations and every high thing that is exalted against the knowledge of God and bringing every thought into captivity to the obedience of the AnointedOne<G5547>;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  10,   6, 'and being in readiness to avenge all disobedience when your obedience is made full.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  10,   7, 'Do you look at things only as they appear in front of your face? If anyone trusts in himself that he is the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s, let him consider this again with himself, that even as he is the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s, so we also are the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  10,   8, 'For even if I boast somewhat abundantly concerning our authority, which the Lord<G2962> gave for building you up, and not for casting you down, I will not be ashamed,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  10,  10, 'For, \"His letters\", they say, \"are weighty and strong, but his bodily presence is weak, and his speech is despised.\"');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  10,  14, 'For we don\'t stretch ourselves too much, as though we didn\'t reach to you. For we came even as far as to you with the Good News of the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,   2, 'For I am jealous over you with a godly jealousy. For I married you to one husband, that I might present you as a pure virgin to the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,   3, 'But I am afraid that somehow, as the serpent deceived Eve in his craftiness, so your minds might be corrupted from the simplicity that is in the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,   4, 'For if someone preaches another Jesus, whom we did not preach, or if you receive a different spirit, which you didn\'t receive, or a different \"good news\", which you did not accept, you put up with that well enough.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  10, 'As the truth of the AnointedOne<G5547> is in me, no one will stop me from this boasting in the regions of Achaia.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  11, 'Why? Because I don\'t love<G0025> you? God knows!');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  12, 'But what I do, that I will do, that I may cut off occasion from those who desire an occasion, that in which they boast, they may be found even as we.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  13, 'For such men are false apostles, deceitful workers, masquerading as the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s apostles.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  15, 'So it is no great thing if his servants also masquerade as servants of righteousness, whose end will be according to their actions.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  18, 'Seeing that many boast according to the flesh, I will also boast.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  20, 'For you bear with a man if he brings you into slavery, if he devours you, if he takes you captive, if he exalts himself, or if he strikes you on the face.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  21, 'I speak by way of disparagement, as though we had been weak. Yet in whatever way anyone is bold (I speak in foolishness), I am bold also.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  23, 'Are they servants of the AnointedOne<G5547>? (I speak as one beside himself.) I am more so: in labors more abundantly, in prisons more abundantly, in stripes above measure, and in deaths often.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  24, 'Five times I received forty stripes minus one from the Jews.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  28, 'Besides those things that are outside, there is that which presses on me daily: anxiety for all the assemblies.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  31, 'The God and Father of the Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, he who is blessed for evermore, knows that I don\'t lie.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  32, 'In Damascus the governor under King Aretas guarded the Damascenes\' city, desiring to arrest me.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  11,  33, 'I was let down in a basket through a window by the wall, and escaped his hands.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,   2, 'I know a man in the AnointedOne<G5547> who, fourteen years ago, was caught up into the third heaven (whether in the body or out of the body, I don\'t know; God knows).');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,   6, 'For if I would desire to boast, I will not be foolish; for I will speak the truth. But I refrain, so that no man may think more of me than that which he sees in me or hears from me.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,   7, 'By reason of the exceeding greatness of the revelations, that I should not be exalted excessively, a thorn in the flesh was given to me: a messenger of Satan to torment me, that I should not be exalted excessively.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,   9, 'He has said to me, \"My grace is sufficient for you, for my power is made perfect in weakness.\" So I will rather glory in my weaknesses most gladly, that the power of the AnointedOne<G5547> may rest on me.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,  10, 'So I take pleasure in weaknesses, in injuries, in necessities, in persecutions, and in distresses, for AnointedOne<G5547>\'s sake. For when I am weak, then am I strong.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,  11, 'I have become foolish in boasting. You compelled me, for I ought to have been commended by you, for I am in no way inferior to the very best apostles, though I am nothing.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,  12, 'Truly the signs of an apostle were worked among you in all perseverance, in signs and wonders and mighty acts.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,  15, 'I will most gladly spend and be spent for your souls. If I love<G0025> you more abundantly, am I loved<G0025> the less?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,  16, 'Even so, I myself didn\'t burden you. \"But, being crafty, I caught you with deception.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,  17, 'Did I take advantage of you by any of those whom I sent to you?');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,  19, 'Again, do you think that we are excusing ourselves to you? In the sight of God we speak in the AnointedOne<G5547>. But all things, dear-ones<G0027>, are for your edifying.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,  20, 'For I am afraid that by any means, when I come, I might find you not the way I want to, and that I might be found by you as you don\'t desire, that by any means there would be strife, jealousy, outbursts of anger, factions, slander, whisperings, proud thoughts, or riots,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  12,  21, 'that again when I come my God would humble me before you, and I would mourn for many of those who have sinned before now, and not repented of the uncleanness, sexual immorality, and lustfulness which they committed.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  13,   3, 'seeing that you seek a proof of the AnointedOne<G5547> who speaks in me; who toward you is not weak, but is powerful in you.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  13,   5, 'Examine yourselves, whether you are in the faith. Test yourselves. Or don\'t you know about your own selves, that Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> is in you? Unless indeed you are disqualified!');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  13,   9, 'For we rejoice when we are weak and you are strong. We also pray for this: your becoming perfect.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  13,  11, 'Finally, brothers, rejoice! Be perfected. Be comforted. Be of the same mind. Live in peace, and the God of love<G0026> and peace will be with you.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2CO',  13,  14, 'The grace of the Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, the love<G0026> of God, and the fellowship of the Holy Spirit, be with you all. Amen.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,   1, 'Paul, an apostle- not from men, nor through man, but through Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, and God the Father, who raised him from the dead-');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,   3, 'Grace to you and peace from God the Father and our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,   4, 'who gave himself for our sins, that he might deliver us out of this present evil age, according to the will of our God and Father-');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,   6, 'I marvel that you are so quickly deserting him who called you in the grace of the AnointedOne<G5547> to a different \"good news\";');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,   7, 'but there isn\'t another \"good news.\" Only there are some who trouble you and want to pervert the Good News of AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,  10, 'For am I now seeking the favor of men, or of God? Or am I striving to please men? For if I were still pleasing men, I wouldn\'t be a servant of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,  12, 'For I didn\'t receive it from man, nor was I taught it, but it came to me through revelation of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,  13, 'For you have heard of my way of living in time past in the Jews\' religion, how that beyond measure I persecuted the assembly of God and ravaged it.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,  15, 'But when it was the good pleasure of God, who separated me from my mother\'s womb and called me through his grace');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,  19, 'But of the other apostles I saw no one except James, the Lord<G2962>\'s brother.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,  22, 'I was still unknown by face to the assemblies of Judea which were in the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   1,  24, 'So they glorified God in me.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,   4, 'This was because of the false brothers secretly brought in, who stole in to spy out our liberty which we have in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus, that they might bring us into slavery,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,   6, 'But from those who were reputed to be important- whatever they were, it makes no difference to me; God doesn\'t show partiality to man- they, I say, who were respected imparted nothing to me,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,   7, 'but to the contrary, when they saw that I had been entrusted with the Good News for the uncircumcised, even as Peter with the Good News for the circumcised');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,   8, 'for he who worked through Peter in the apostleship with the circumcised also worked through me with the Gentiles -');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,   9, 'and when they perceived the grace that was given to me, James and Cephas and John, those who were reputed to be pillars, gave to Barnabas and me the right hand of fellowship, that we should go to the Gentiles, and they to the circumcision.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,  10, 'They only asked us to remember the poor - which very thing I was also zealous to do.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,  13, 'And the rest of the Jews joined him in his hypocrisy, so that even Barnabas was carried away with their hypocrisy.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,  16, 'yet knowing that a man is not justified by the actions of the law but through faith in Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, even we believed in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus, that we might be justified by faith in the AnointedOne<G5547>, and not by the actions of the law, because no flesh will be justified by the actions of the law.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,  17, 'But if while we sought to be justified in the AnointedOne<G5547>, we ourselves also were found to be sinners, is the AnointedOne<G5547> a servant of sin? Certainly not!');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,  20, 'I have been crucified with the AnointedOne<G5547>, and it is no longer I who live, but the AnointedOne<G5547> living in me. That life which I now live in the flesh, I live by faith in the Son of God, who loved<G0025> me, and gave himself up for me.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   2,  21, 'I don\'t reject the grace of God. For if righteousness is through the law, then the AnointedOne<G5547> died for nothing!\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,   1, 'Foolish Galatians, who has bewitched you not to obey the truth, before whose eyes Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> was openly portrayed among you as crucified?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,   2, 'I just want to learn this from you: Did you receive the Spirit by the works of the law, or by hearing of faith?');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,   5, 'So he who supplies the Spirit to you and does miracles among you, does he do it by the works of the law, or by hearing of faith?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,   6, 'Just as Abraham \"believed God, and it was counted to him for righteousness.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,   7, 'So know that those who are of faith are children of Abraham.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,  10, 'For as many as are of the works of the law are under a curse. For it is written, \"Cursed is everyone who doesn\'t continue in all things that are written in the book of the law, to do them.\"');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,  13, 'The AnointedOne<G5547> redeemed us from the curse of the law, having become a curse for us. For it is written, \"Cursed is everyone who hangs on a tree\",');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,  14, 'that the blessing of Abraham might come on the Gentiles through AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus, that we might receive the promise of the Spirit through faith.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,  15, 'Brothers, speaking of human terms, though it is only a man\'s covenant, yet when it has been confirmed, no one makes it void or adds to it.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,  16, 'Now the promises were spoken to Abraham and to his offspring. He doesn\'t say, \"To descendants\", as of many, but as of one, \"To your offspring\", which is the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,  17, 'Now I say this: A covenant confirmed beforehand by God in the AnointedOne<G5547>, the law, which came four hundred thirty years after, does not annul, so as to make the promise of no effect.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,  24, 'So that the law has become our tutor to bring us to the AnointedOne<G5547>, that we might be justified by faith.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,  27, 'For as many of you as were baptized into the AnointedOne<G5547> have put on the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   3,  29, 'If you are the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s, then you are Abraham\'s offspring and heirs according to promise.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,   1, 'But I say that so long as the heir is a child, he is no different from a bondservant, though he is Lord<G2962> of all,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,   5, 'that he might redeem those who were under the law, that we might receive the adoption as children.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,   7, 'So you are no longer a bondservant, but a son; and if a son, then an heir of God through the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,  13, 'but you know that because of weakness in the flesh I preached the Good News to you the first time.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,  19, 'My little children, of whom I am again in childbirth until the AnointedOne<G5547> is formed in you -');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,  22, 'For it is written that Abraham had two sons, one by the servant, and one by the free woman.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,  23, 'However, the son by the servant was born according to the flesh, but the son by the free woman was born through promise.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,  27, 'For it is written, \"Rejoice, you barren who don\'t bear. Break forth and shout, you that aren\'t in labor. For more are the children of the desolate than of her who has a husband.\"');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,  29, 'But just as he who was born according to the flesh persecuted him who was born according to the Spirit, so also it is now.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,  30, 'However what does the Scripture say? \"Throw out the servant and her son, for the son of the servant will not inherit with the son of the free woman.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   4,  31, 'So then, brothers, we are not children of a servant, but of the free woman.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,   1, 'For freedom the AnointedOne<G5547> has made us free; so stand firm and don\'t be entangled again with a yoke of slavery.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,   2, 'Behold, I, Paul, tell you that if you receive circumcision, the AnointedOne<G5547> will profit you nothing.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,   3, 'Yes, I testify again to every man who receives circumcision that he is a debtor to do the whole law.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,   4, 'You are alienated from the AnointedOne<G5547>, you who desire to be justified by the law. You have fallen away from grace.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,   6, 'For in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus neither circumcision amounts to anything, nor uncircumcision, but faith working through love<G0026>.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,  13, 'For you, brothers, were called for freedom. Only don\'t use your freedom for gain to the flesh, but through love<G0026> be servants to one another.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,  17, 'For the desires of the flesh are against the Spirit, and the Spirit against the flesh; and these are contrary to one another, that you may not do the things that you desire.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,  19, 'Now the actions of the flesh are obvious, which are: adultery, sexual immorality, uncleanness, lustfulness,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,  21, 'envy, murders, drunkenness, orgies, and things like these; of which I forewarn you, even as I also forewarned you, that those who practice such things will not inherit God\'s Kingdom.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   5,  24, 'Those who belong to the AnointedOne<G5547> have crucified the flesh with its passions and lusts.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   6,   2, 'Bear one another\'s burdens, and so fulfill the law of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   6,   4, 'But let each man examine his own work, and then he will have reason to boast in himself, and not in someone else.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   6,  12, 'As many as desire to make a good impression in the flesh compel you to be circumcised; just so they may not be persecuted for the cross of AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('GAL',   6,  15, 'For in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus neither circumcision nor uncircumcision is anything, but [being] a new creation.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,   3, 'Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, who has blessed us with every spiritual blessing in the heavenly places in the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,   4, 'even as he chose us in him before the foundation of the world, that we would be holy and without blemish before him in love<G0026>,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,   6, 'to the praise of the glory of his grace, by which he freely gave us favor in the Dear-ones<G0027>,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,  10, 'to an administration of the fullness of the times, to sum up all things in the AnointedOne<G5547>, the things in the heavens and the things on the earth, in him.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,  11, 'We were also assigned an inheritance in him, having been foreordained according to the purpose of him who does all things after the counsel of his will,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,  12, 'to the end that we should be to the praise of his glory, we who had before hoped in the AnointedOne<G5547>:');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,  13, 'in whom you also, having heard the word of the truth, the Good News of your salvation - in whom, having also believed, you were sealed with the promised Holy Spirit,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,  15, 'For this cause I also, having heard of the faith in the Lord<G2962> Jesus which is among you, and the love<G0026> which you have toward all the saints,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,  17, 'that the God of our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, the Father of glory, may give to you a spirit of wisdom and revelation in the knowledge of him,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,  20, 'which he worked in the AnointedOne<G5547>, when he raised him from the dead and made him to sit at his right hand in the heavenly places,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   1,  21, 'far above all rule, authority, power, dominion, and every name that is named, not only in this age, but also in that which is to come.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,   2, 'in which you once walked according to the course of this world, according to the prince of the power of the air, the spirit who now works in the children of disobedience;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,   3, 'among whom we also all once lived in the lusts of our flesh, doing the desires of the flesh and of the mind, and were by nature children of wrath, even as the rest.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,   4, 'But God, being rich in mercy, for his great love<G0026> with which he loved<G0025> us,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,   5, 'even when we were dead through our trespasses, made us alive together with the AnointedOne<G5547> (by grace you have been saved),');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,   9, 'not of actions, that no one would boast.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,  10, 'For we are his workmanship, created in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus for good actions, which God prepared before that we would walk in them.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,  11, 'So remember that once you, the Gentiles in the flesh, who are called \"uncircumcision\" by that which is called \"circumcision\" (in the flesh, made by hands),');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,  12, 'that you were at that time separate from the AnointedOne<G5547>, alienated from the commonwealth of Israel, and strangers from the covenants of the promise, having no hope and without God in the world.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,  13, 'But now in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus you who once were far off are made near in the blood of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,  14, 'For he is our peace, who made both one, and broke the barrier of hostility,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,  15, 'having abolished in his flesh the hostility, the law of commandments contained in ordinances, that he might create in himself one new man of the two, making peace,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,  16, 'and might reconcile them both in one body to God through the cross, having killed the hostility by it.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   2,  19, 'So then you are no longer strangers and foreigners, but you are fellow citizens with the saints and of the household of God,');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,   2, 'if it is so that you have heard of the administration of that grace of God which was given me toward you,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,   3, 'how that by revelation the mystery was made known to me, as I wrote before in few words.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,   4, 'By which, when you read, you can perceive my understanding in the mystery of the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,   5, 'which in other generations was not made known to the children of men, as it has now been revealed to his holy apostles and prophets in the Spirit.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,   6, 'The Gentiles are fellow heirs and fellow members of the body, and fellow partakers of his promise in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus through the Good News,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,   7, 'of which I was made a servant according to the gift of that grace of God which was given me according to the working of his power.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,   8, 'To me, the very least of all saints, was this grace given, to preach to the Gentiles the unsearchable riches of the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,   9, 'and to make all men see what is the administration of the mystery which for ages has been hidden in God, who created all things through Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,  11, 'according to the eternal purpose which he accomplished in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus our Lord<G2962>;');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,  16, 'that he would grant you, according to the riches of his glory, that you may be strengthened with power through his Spirit in the inner person,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,  17, 'that the AnointedOne<G5547> may dwell in your hearts through faith, to the end that you, being rooted and grounded in love<G0026>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,  18, 'may be strengthened to comprehend with all the saints what is the width and length and height and depth,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,  19, 'and to know the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s love<G0026> which surpasses knowledge, that you may be filled with all the fullness of God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   3,  20, 'Now to him who is able to do exceedingly abundantly above all that we ask or think, according to the power that works in us,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,   1, 'So I, the prisoner in the Lord<G2962>, beg you to walk worthily of the calling with which you were called,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,   2, 'with all lowliness and humility, with patience, bearing with one another in love<G0026>,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,   4, 'There is one body and one Spirit, even as you also were called in one hope of your calling,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,   6, 'one God and Father of all, who is over all and through all, and in us all.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,   7, 'But to each one of us the grace was given, according to the measure of the gift of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,   9, 'Now this, \"He ascended\", what is it but that he also first descended into the lower parts of the earth?');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  11, 'And He also gave some to be apostles; and some, prophets; and some, evangelists; and some, shepherds and teachers;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  12, 'for the perfecting of the saints, to the work of serving, to the building up of the body of the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  13, 'until we all attain to the unity of the faith and of the knowledge of the Son of God, to a full grown man, to the measure of the stature of the fullness of the AnointedOne<G5547>;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  15, 'but speaking truth in love<G0026>, we may grow up in all things into him who is the head, the AnointedOne<G5547>;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  16, 'from whom all the body, being fitted and knit together through that which every joint supplies, according to the working in measure of each individual part, makes the body increase to the building up of itself in love<G0026>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  17, 'So this I say, and testify in the Lord<G2962>, that you no longer walk as the rest of the Gentiles also walk, in the futility of their mind,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  18, 'being darkened in their understanding, alienated from the life of God because of the ignorance that is in them, because of the hardening of their hearts.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  19, 'They, having become callous, gave themselves up to lust, to work all uncleanness with greediness.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  20, 'But you didn\'t learn the AnointedOne<G5547> that way,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  22, 'that you put away, as concerning your former way of life, the old man that grows corrupt after the lusts of deceit,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  25, 'So, putting away falsehood, speak truth each one with his neighbor. For we are members of one another.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  27, 'and don\'t give place to the devil.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  28, 'Let him who stole steal no more; but rather let him labor, producing with his hands something that is good, that he may have something to give to him who has need.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  29, 'Let no rotten<G4550> speech proceed out of your mouth, but only what is good for building others up as the need may be, that it may give grace to those who hear.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  31, 'Let all bitterness, wrath, anger, outcry, and slander be put away from you, along with all malice.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   4,  32, 'And be kind to one another, tender-hearted, forgiving each other, just as God also in the AnointedOne<G5547> forgave you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,   1, 'So be imitators of God, as dear<G0027> children.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,   2, 'Walk in love<G0026>, even as the AnointedOne<G5547> also loved<G0025> us and gave himself up for us, an offering and a sacrifice to God for a sweet-smelling fragrance.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,   3, 'But sexual immorality, and all uncleanness or covetousness, let it not even be mentioned among you, as becomes saints;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,   4, 'nor filthiness, nor foolish talking, nor jesting, which are not appropriate, but rather giving of thanks.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,   5, 'Know this for sure, that no sexually immoral person, nor unclean person, nor covetous man, who is an idolater, has any inheritance in the Kingdom of the AnointedOne<G5547> and God.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,   7, 'So don\'t be partakers with them.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  11, 'Have no fellowship with the unfruitful actions of darkness, but rather even reprove them.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  12, 'For it is a shame even to speak of the things which they do in secret.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  14, 'So he says, \"Awake, you who sleep, and arise from the dead, and the AnointedOne<G5547> will shine on you.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  15, 'So watch carefully how you walk, not as unwise, but as wise,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  17, 'So don\'t be foolish, but understand what the will of the Lord<G2962> is.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  19, 'speaking to one another in psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs; singing and making melody in your heart to the Lord<G2962>;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  21, 'subjecting yourselves to one another in the fear of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  23, 'For the husband is the head of the wife, as the AnointedOne<G5547> is the head of the assembly, being himself the savior of the body.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  24, 'But as the assembly is subject to the AnointedOne<G5547>, so let the wives also be to their own husbands in everything.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  25, 'Husbands, love<G0025> your wives, even as the AnointedOne<G5547> also loved<G0025> the assembly, and gave himself up for it;');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  28, 'Even so husbands also ought to love<G0025> their own wives as their own bodies. He who loves<G0025> his own wife loves<G0025> himself.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  31, '\"For this a man will leave his father and mother, and will be joined to his wife. Then the two will become one flesh.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   5,  32, 'This mystery is great, but I speak concerning the AnointedOne<G5547> and of the assembly.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,   5, 'Servants, be obedient to those who according to the flesh are your masters<G2962>, with fear and trembling, in singleness of your heart, as to the AnointedOne<G5547>;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,   6, 'not in the way of service only when eyes are on you, as men pleasers, but as servants of the AnointedOne<G5547>, doing the will of God from the heart;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,   7, 'with good will doing service as to the Lord<G2962>, and not to men,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,   8, 'knowing that whatever good each of us does, he will be repaid by the Lord<G2962>, whether he is bound or free.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,   9, 'You masters<G2962>, do the same things to them, and give up threatening, knowing that he who is both their Master<G2962> and yours is in heaven, and there is no partiality with him.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,  13, 'So put on the whole armor of God, that you may be able to withstand in the evil day, and having done all, to stand.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,  14, 'Stand therefore, having the belt of truth buckled around your waist, and having put on the breastplate of righteousness,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,  15, 'and having fitted your feet with the preparation of the Good News of peace,');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,  21, 'But that you also may know my affairs, how I am doing, Tychicus, the dear<G0027> brother and faithful servant in the Lord<G2962>, will make known to you all things.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,  22, 'I have sent him to you for this very purpose, that you may know about us and that he may comfort your hearts.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,  23, 'Peace be to the brothers, and love<G0026> with faith, from God the Father and the Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('EPH',   6,  24, 'Grace be with all those who love<G0025> our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> with incorruptibility. Amen.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,   2, 'Grace to you, and peace from God our Father and the Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,   4, 'always in every request of mine on behalf of you all, making my requests with joy,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,   7, 'It is even right for me to think this way on behalf of all of you, because I have you in my heart, because both in my bonds and in the defense and confirmation of the Good News, you all are partakers with me of grace.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,   9, 'This I pray, that your love<G0026> may abound yet more and more in knowledge and all discernment,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  10, 'so that you may approve the things that are excellent, that you may be sincere and without offense to the day of the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  12, 'Now I desire to have you know, brothers, that the things which happened to me have turned out rather to the progress of the Good News,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  13, 'so that it became evident to the whole palace guard, and to all the rest, that my bonds are in the AnointedOne<G5547>;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  15, 'Some indeed preach the AnointedOne<G5547> even out of envy and strife, and some also out of good will.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  16, 'The former insincerely preach the AnointedOne<G5547> from selfish ambition, thinking that they add affliction to my chains;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  17, 'but the latter out of love<G0026>, knowing that I am appointed for the defense of the Good News.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  18, 'What does it matter? Only that in every way, whether in pretense or in truth, the AnointedOne<G5547> is proclaimed. I rejoice in this, yes, and will rejoice.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  19, 'For I know that this will turn out to my salvation, through your prayers and the supply of the Spirit of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  20, 'according to my earnest expectation and hope, that I will in no way be disappointed, but with all boldness, as always, now also the AnointedOne<G5547> will be magnified in my body, whether by life or by death.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  21, 'For to me to live is the AnointedOne<G5547>, and to die is gain.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  23, 'But I am in a dilemma between the two, having the desire to depart and be with the AnointedOne<G5547>, which is far better.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  24, 'Yet to remain in the flesh is more needful for your sake.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  25, 'Having this confidence, I know that I will remain, yes, and remain with you all for your progress and joy in the faith,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  27, 'Only let your way of life be worthy of the Good News of the AnointedOne<G5547>, that, whether I come and see you or am absent, I may hear of your state, that you stand firm in one spirit, with one soul striving for the faith of the Good News;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  29, 'Because it has been granted to you on behalf of the AnointedOne<G5547>, not only to believe in him, but also to suffer on his behalf,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   1,  30, 'having the same conflict which you saw in me and now hear is in me.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,   1, 'So if there is any exhortation in the AnointedOne<G5547>, if any consolation of love<G0026>, if any fellowship of the Spirit, if any tender mercies and compassion,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,   2, 'fulfil my joy by being like-minded, having the same love<G0026>, being of one accord, of one mind.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,   3, 'Do nothing through rivalry or conceit, but in humility, each counting others better than themselves.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,   4, 'Let each of you not only look after yourselves, but also look after others.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,   8, 'And being found in human form, he humbled himself, becoming obedient; obedient to the point of death. Even death on a cross.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,   9, 'So God also highly exalted him, and gave to him the name which is above every name,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  13, 'For it is God who works in you both to will and to work, for his good pleasure.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  14, 'Do all things without complaining and arguing,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  16, 'holding up the word of life, that I may have something to boast in the day of the AnointedOne<G5547>, that I didn\'t run in vain nor labor in vain.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  22, 'But you know the proof of him, that as a child serves a father, so he served with me in furtherance of the Good News.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  23, 'So I hope to send him at once, as soon as I see how it will go with me.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  25, 'But I counted it necessary to send to you Epaphroditus, my brother, fellow worker, fellow soldier, and your apostle and servant of my need,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  26, 'since he longed for you all, and was very troubled because you had heard that he was sick.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  27, 'For indeed he was sick, nearly to death, but God had mercy on him, and not on him only, but on me also, that I might not have sorrow upon sorrow.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  28, 'So I have sent him the more diligently, that when you see him again, you may rejoice, and that I may be the less sorrowful.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  29, 'So receive him in the Lord<G2962> with all joy, and hold such people in honor,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   2,  30, 'because for the work of the AnointedOne<G5547> he came near to death, risking his life to supply that which was lacking in your service toward me.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,   1, 'Finally, my brothers, rejoice in the Lord<G2962>! To write the same things to you, to me indeed is not tiresome, but for you it is safe.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,   7, 'However, those things that were gain to me, I now consider as damage<G2209> on account of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,   8, 'Yes most certainly, and I count all things as damage<G2209> for the excellency of the knowledge of AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus, my Lord<G2962>, for whom I suffered the loss of all things, and count them nothing but filth<G4657>, that I may gain the AnointedOne<G5547>');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,   9, 'and be found in him, not having a righteousness of my own, that which is of the law, but that which is through faith in the AnointedOne<G5547>, the righteousness which is from God by faith,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,  10, 'that I may know him, and the power of his resurrection, and the fellowship of his sufferings, becoming conformed to his death,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,  12, 'Not that I have already obtained, or am already made perfect; but I press on, so that I may take hold of that for which also I was taken hold of by AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,  13, 'Brothers, I don\'t regard myself as yet having taken hold, but one thing I do: forgetting the things which are behind, and stretching forward to the things which are before,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,  15, 'So let us, as many as are perfect, think this way. If in anything you think otherwise, God will also reveal that to you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,  16, 'Nevertheless, to the extent that we have already attained, let\'s walk by the same rule. Let us be of the same mind.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,  18, 'For many walk, of whom I told you often, and now tell you even weeping, as the enemies of the cross of the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   3,  20, 'For our citizenship is in heaven, from where we also wait for a Savior, the Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   4,   1, 'So, my brothers, dear<G0027> and longed for, my joy and crown, in this way stand firm in the Lord<G2962> loved-ones<G0027>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   4,   3, 'Yes, I beg you also, true partner, help these women, for they labored with me in the Good News with Clement also, and the rest of my fellow workers, whose names are in the book of life.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   4,   4, 'Rejoice in the Lord<G2962> always! Again I say, \"Rejoice!\"');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   4,   8, 'Finally, brothers, whatever things are true, whatever things are honorable, whatever things are just, whatever things are pure, whatever things are lovely, whatever things are of good report: if there is any virtue, and if there is any praise, think about these things.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   4,  11, 'Not that I speak because of lack, for I have learned in whatever state I am, to be content in it.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   4,  12, 'I know how to be humbled, and I also know how to abound. In everything and in all things I have learned the secret both to be filled and to be hungry, both to abound and to be in need.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   4,  13, 'I can do all things through the AnointedOne<G5547>, who strengthens me.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHP',   4,  18, 'But I have all things and abound. I am filled, having received from Epaphroditus the things that came from you, a sweet-smelling fragrance, an acceptable and well-pleasing sacrifice to God.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,   2, 'to the saints and faithful brothers in the AnointedOne<G5547> at Colossae: Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,   4, 'having heard of your faith in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus and of the love<G0026> which you have toward all the saints,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,   5, 'because of the hope which is laid up for you in the heavens, of which you heard before in the word of the truth of the Good News');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,   6, 'which has come to you, even as it is in all the world and is bearing fruit and growing, as it does in you also, since the day you heard and knew the grace of God in truth,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,   7, 'even as you learned of Epaphras our dear<G0027> fellow servant, who is a faithful servant of the AnointedOne<G5547> on our behalf,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,   8, 'who also declared to us your love<G0026> in the Spirit.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  10, 'that you may walk worthily of the Lord<G2962>, to please him in all respects, bearing fruit in every good work and increasing in the knowledge of God,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  11, 'strengthened with all power, according to the might of his glory, for all endurance and perseverance with joy,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  12, 'giving thanks to the Father, who made us fit to be partakers of the inheritance of the saints in light,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  13, 'who delivered us out of the power of darkness, and translated us into the Kingdom of the Son of his love<G0026>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  14, 'in whom we have our redemption, the forgiveness of our sins.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  15, 'He is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn of all creation.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  16, 'For by him all things were created in the heavens and on the earth, visible things and invisible things, whether thrones or dominions or principalities or powers. All things have been created through him and for him.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  18, 'He is the head of the body, the assembly, who is the beginning, the firstborn from the dead, that in all things he might have the preeminence.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  19, 'For all the fullness was pleased to dwell in him,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  20, 'and through him to reconcile all things to himself by him, whether things on the earth or things in the heavens, having made peace through the blood of his cross.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  21, 'You, being in past times alienated and enemies in your mind in your evil actions,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  23, 'if it is so that you continue in the faith, grounded and steadfast, and not moved away from the hope of the Good News which you heard, which is being proclaimed in all creation under heaven, of which I, Paul, was made a servant.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  24, 'Now I rejoice in my sufferings for your sake, and fill up on my part that which is lacking of the afflictions of the AnointedOne<G5547> in my flesh for his body\'s sake, which is the assembly,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  25, 'of which I was made a servant according to the stewardship of God which was given me toward you to fulfill the word of God,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  27, 'to whom God was pleased to make known what are the riches of the glory of this mystery among the Gentiles, which is the AnointedOne<G5547> in you, the hope of glory.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   1,  29, 'for which I also labor, striving according to his working, which works in me mightily.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,   2, 'that their hearts may be comforted, they being knit together in love<G0026>, and gaining all riches of the full assurance of understanding, that they may know the mystery of God, both of the Father and of the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,   3, 'in whom all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge are hidden.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,   4, 'Now I say this that no one may delude you with persuasiveness of speech.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,   5, 'For though I am absent in the flesh, yet I am with you in the spirit, rejoicing and seeing your order, and the steadfastness of your faith in the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,   6, 'So, as you received AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus, the Lord<G2962>, walk in him,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,   8, 'Be careful that you don\'t let anyone rob you through his philosophy and vain deceit, after the tradition of men, after the elements of the world, and not after the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,   9, 'For in him all the fullness of Deity dwells bodily,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,  10, 'and in him you are made full, who is the head of all principality and power.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,  11, 'In him you were also circumcised with a circumcision not made with hands, in the putting off of the body of the sins of the flesh, in the circumcision of the AnointedOne<G5547>,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,  14, 'wiping out the handwriting in ordinances which was against us. He has taken it out of the way, nailing it to the cross.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,  15, 'Having stripped the principalities and the powers, he made a show of them openly, triumphing over them in it.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,  16, 'So, let no one judge you in eating, or in drinking, or with respect to a feast day or a new moon or a Sabbath day,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,  17, 'which are a shadow of the things to come; but the body is the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,  18, 'Let no one rob you of your prize by self-abasement and worshiping of the angels, dwelling in the things which he has not seen, vainly puffed up by his fleshly mind,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,  20, 'If you died with the AnointedOne<G5547> from the elements of the world, why, as though living in the world, do you subject yourselves to ordinances,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   2,  23, 'These things indeed appear like wisdom in self-imposed worship, humility, and severity to the body; but aren\'t of any value against the indulgence of the flesh.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,   1, 'If then you were raised together with the AnointedOne<G5547>, seek the things that are above, where the AnointedOne<G5547> is, seated on the right hand of God.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,   3, 'For you died, and your life is hidden with the AnointedOne<G5547> in God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,   4, 'When the AnointedOne<G5547>, our life, is revealed, then you will also be revealed with him in glory.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,   5, 'So, put to death your members which are on the earth: sexual immorality, uncleanness, depraved passion, evil desire, and covetousness, which is idolatry.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,   6, 'For the sake of these things, wrath of God comes on the children of disobedience.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,  11, 'where there can\'t be Greek and Jew, circumcision and uncircumcision, barbarian, Scythian, bondservant, freeman; but the AnointedOne<G5547> is all, and in all.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,  12, 'So, put on a heart of compassion, kindness, lowliness, humility, and perseverance, as God\'s chosen ones holy and loved<G0025>;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,  13, 'bearing with one another, and forgiving each other, if any man has a complaint against any; even as the AnointedOne<G5547> forgave you, so you also do.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,  14, 'Above all these things, walk in love<G0026>, which is the bond of perfection.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,  15, 'And let the peace of God rule in your hearts, to which also you were called in one body, and be thankful.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,  16, 'Let the word of the AnointedOne<G5547> dwell in you richly; in all wisdom teaching and admonishing one another with psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs, singing with grace in your heart to the Lord<G2962>.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,  22, 'Servants, obey in all things those who are your masters<G2962> according to the flesh, not just when they are looking, as men pleasers, but in singleness of heart, fearing God.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   3,  24, 'knowing that from the Lord<G2962> you will receive the reward of the inheritance; for you serve the Lord<G2962> the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,   1, 'Masters<G2962>, give to your servants that which is just and equal, knowing that you also have a Master<G2962> in heaven.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,   2, 'Continue steadfastly in prayer, watching in it with thanksgiving,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,   3, 'praying together for us also, that God may open to us a door for the word, to speak the mystery of the AnointedOne<G5547>, for which I am also in bonds,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,   7, 'All my affairs will be made known to you by Tychicus, the dear<G0027> brother, faithful servant, and fellow bondservant in the Lord<G2962>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,   9, 'together with Onesimus, the faithful and dear<G0027> brother, who is one of you. They will make known to you everything that is going on here.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,  11, 'and Jesus called Justus. These are my only fellow workers for God\'s Kingdom who are of the circumcision, men who have been a comfort to me.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,  12, 'Epaphras, who is one of you, a servant of the AnointedOne<G5547>, salutes you, always striving for you in his prayers, that you may stand perfect and complete in all the will of God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,  13, 'For I testify about him that he has great zeal for you, and for those in Laodicea, and for those in Hierapolis.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,  14, 'Luke, the dear<G0027> physician, and Demas greet you.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('COL',   4,  16, 'When this letter has been read among you, cause it to be read also in the assembly of the Laodiceans, and that you also read the letter from Laodicea.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   1,   3, 'remembering without ceasing your work of faith and labor of love<G0026> and perseverance of hope in our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, before our God and Father.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   1,   4, 'We know, brothers loved<G0025> by God, that you are chosen,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   1,   8, 'For from you the word of the Lord<G2962> has been declared, not only in Macedonia and Achaia, but also in every place your faith toward God has gone out, so that we need not to say anything.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   1,   9, 'For they themselves report concerning us what kind of a reception we had from you, and how you turned to God from idols, to serve a living and true God,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   1,  10, 'and to wait for his Son from heaven, whom he raised from the dead: Jesus, who delivers us from the wrath to come.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   2,   4, 'But even as we have been approved by God to be entrusted with the Good News, so we speak: not as pleasing men, but God, who tests our hearts.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   2,   6, 'nor seeking glory from men (neither from you nor from others), when we might have claimed authority as apostles of the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   2,   8, 'Even so, affectionately longing for you, we were well pleased to impart to you, not the Good News of God only, but also our own souls, because you had become very dear<G0027> to us.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   2,  10, 'You are witnesses with God how holy, righteously, and blamelessly we behaved ourselves toward you who believe.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   2,  13, 'For this cause we also thank God without ceasing, that when you received from us the word of the message of God, you accepted it not as the word of men, but as it is in truth, the word of God, which also works in you who believe.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   2,  14, 'For you, brothers, became imitators of the assemblies of God which are in Judea in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus; for you also suffered the same things from your own countrymen, even as they did from the Jews');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   2,  15, 'who killed both the Lord<G2962> Jesus and their own prophets, and drove us out, and don\'t please God, and are contrary to all men,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   2,  16, 'forbidding us to speak to the Gentiles that they may be saved, to fill up their sins always. But wrath has come on them to the uttermost.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   2,  18, 'because we wanted to come to you - indeed, I, Paul, once and again - but Satan hindered us.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   3,   1, 'So when we couldn\'t stand it any longer, we thought it good to be left behind at Athens alone,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   3,   2, 'and sent Timothy, our brother and God\'s servant in the Good News of the AnointedOne<G5547>, to establish you, and to comfort you concerning your faith,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   3,   3, 'that no one would be moved by these afflictions. For you know that we are appointed to this task.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   3,   6, 'But when Timothy came just now to us from you, and brought us glad news of your faith and love<G0026>, and that you have good memories of us always, longing to see us, even as we also long to see you,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   3,   9, 'For what thanksgiving can we render again to God for you, for all the joy with which we rejoice for your sakes before our God,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   3,  11, 'Now may our God and Father himself, and our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, direct our way to you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   3,  12, 'May the Lord<G2962> make you to increase and abound in love<G0026> toward one another, and toward all men, even as we also do toward you,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   3,  13, 'to the end he may establish your hearts blameless in holiness before our God and Father at the coming of our Lord<G2962> Jesus with all his saints.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   4,   4, 'that each one of you know how to control his own body in sanctification and honor,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   4,   5, 'not in the passion of lust, even as the Gentiles who don\'t know God,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   4,   8, 'So he who rejects this doesn\'t reject man, but God, who has also given his Holy Spirit to you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   4,   9, 'But concerning brotherly love, you have no need that one write to you. For you yourselves are taught by God to love<G0025> one another,');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   4,  15, 'For this we tell you by the word of the Lord<G2962>, that we who are alive, who are left until the coming of the Lord<G2962>, will in no way precede those who have fallen asleep.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   4,  16, 'For the Lord<G2962> himself will descend from heaven with a shout, with the voice of the archangel and with God\'s trumpet. The dead in AnointedOne<G5547> will rise first,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   4,  18, 'So comfort one another with these words.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,   5, 'You are all children of light and children of the day. We don\'t belong to the night, nor to darkness,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,   7, 'For those who sleep, sleep in the night; and those who are drunk are drunk in the night.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,   8, 'But since we belong to the day, let\'s be sober, putting on the breastplate of faith and love<G0026>, and for a helmet, the hope of salvation.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,  11, 'So exhort one another, and build each other up, even as you also do.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,  13, 'and to respect and honor them in love<G0026> for their work\'s sake. Be at peace among yourselves.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,  14, 'We exhort you, brothers: Admonish the disorderly; encourage the faint-hearted; support the weak; be patient toward all.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,  15, 'See that no one returns evil for evil to anyone, but pursue all that is good for one another and for all.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,  16, 'Always rejoice.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,  20, 'Don\'t despise prophecies;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TH',   5,  21, 'test all things, and hold firmly that which is good.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   1,   3, 'We are bound to always give thanks to God for you, brothers, even as it is appropriate, because your faith grows exceedingly, and the love<G0026> of each and every one of you towards one another abounds,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   1,   4, 'so that we ourselves boast about you in the assemblies of God for your perseverance and faith in all your persecutions and in the afflictions which you endure.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   1,   5, 'This is an obvious sign of the righteous judgment of God, to the end that you may be counted worthy of God\'s Kingdom, for which you also suffer.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   1,   8, 'punishing those who don\'t know God, and to those who don\'t obey the Good News of our Lord<G2962> Jesus,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   1,  10, 'when he comes in that day to be glorified in his saints and to be admired among all those who have believed, because our testimony to you was believed.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   1,  11, 'To this end we also pray always for you, that our God may count you worthy of your calling, and fulfill every desire of goodness and work of faith with power,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   2,   1, 'Now, brothers, concerning the coming of our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> and our gathering together to him, we ask you');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   2,   2, 'not to be quickly shaken in your mind, nor be troubled, either by spirit, or by word, or by letter as if from us, saying that the day of the AnointedOne<G5547> had come.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   2,   3, 'Let no one deceive you in any way. For it will not be, unless the rebellion comes first, and the man of sin is revealed, the son of destruction,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   2,   4, 'he who opposes and exalts himself against all that is called God or that is worshiped, so that he sits as God in the temple of God, setting himself up as God.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   2,   7, 'For the mystery of lawlessness already works. Only there is one who restrains now, until he is taken out of the way.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   2,  10, 'and with all deception of wickedness for those who are being lost, because they didn\'t receive the love<G0026> of the truth, that they might be saved.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   2,  13, 'But we are bound to always give thanks to God for you, brothers loved<G0025> by the Lord<G2962>, because God chose you from the beginning for salvation through sanctification of the Spirit and belief in the truth,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   2,  15, 'So then, brothers, stand firm and hold the traditions which you were taught by us, whether by word or by letter.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   2,  16, 'Now our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> himself, and God our Father, who loved<G0025> us and gave us eternal comfort and good hope through grace,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   3,   1, 'Finally, brothers, pray for us, that the word of the Lord<G2962> may spread rapidly and be glorified, even as also with you,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   3,   3, 'But the Lord<G2962> is faithful, who will establish you and guard you from the evil one.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   3,   5, 'May the Lord<G2962> direct your hearts into God\'s love<G0026>, and into the perseverance of AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   3,   8, 'neither did we eat bread from anyone\'s hand without paying for it, but with effort and exertion worked night and day, that we might not burden any of you,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   3,  10, 'For even when we were with you, we commanded you this: \"If anyone is not willing to work, don\'t let him eat.\"');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   3,  12, 'Now those who are that way, we command and exhort in the Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, that they work with quietness and eat their own bread.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TH',   3,  13, 'But you, brothers, don\'t lose heart in doing what is right.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,   4, 'neither to pay attention to myths and endless genealogies, which cause disputes, rather than God\'s stewardship, which is in faith -');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,   5, 'but the goal of this command is love<G0026>, out of a pure heart and a good conscience and sincere faith,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,   6, 'from which things some, having missed the mark, have turned away to vain talking,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,   8, 'But we know that the law is good, if one uses it lawfully,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,   9, 'as knowing this, that law is not made for a righteous person, but for the lawless and insubordinate, for the ungodly and sinners, for the unholy and profane, for murderers of fathers and murderers of mothers, for manslayers,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,  10, 'for the sexually immoral, for homosexuals, for slave-traders, for liars, for perjurers, and for any other thing contrary to the sound doctrine,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,  12, 'I thank him who enabled me, AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus our Lord<G2962>, because he counted me faithful, appointing me to service;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,  13, 'although I used to be a blasphemer, a persecutor, and insolent. However, I obtained mercy, because I did it ignorantly in unbelief.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,  15, 'The saying is faithful and worthy of all acceptance, that AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus came into the world to save sinners, of whom I am chief.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,  16, 'However, for this cause I obtained mercy, that in me first, Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> might display all his patience for an example of those who were going to believe in him for eternal life.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,  17, 'Now to the King eternal, permanent<G0862>, invisible, to God who alone is wise, be honor and glory forever and ever. Amen.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,  18, 'I commit this instruction to you, my child Timothy, according to the prophecies which were given to you before, that by them you may wage the good warfare,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,  19, 'holding faith and a good conscience, which some having thrust away made a shipwreck concerning the faith,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   1,  20, 'of whom are Hymenaeus and Alexander, whom I delivered to Satan, that they might be taught not to blaspheme.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,   1, 'So I exhort, first of all, that petitions, prayers, intercessions, and thanksgiving be made for all men:');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,   2, 'for kings and all who are in high places, that we may lead a tranquil and quiet life in all godliness and reverence.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,   3, 'For this is good and acceptable in the sight of God our Savior,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,   6, 'who gave himself as a ransom for all, the testimony in its own times,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,   7, 'to which I was appointed a preacher and an apostle (I am telling the truth in the AnointedOne<G5547>, not lying), a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and truth.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,   8, 'So I desire that the men in every place pray, lifting up holy hands without anger and doubting.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,   9, 'In the same way, that women also adorn themselves in decent clothing, with modesty and propriety, not just with braided hair, gold, pearls, or expensive clothing,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,  10, 'but with good actions, which is appropriate for women professing godliness.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,  11, 'Let a woman learn in quietness with full submission.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,  13, 'For Adam was formed first, then Eve.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   2,  15, 'but she will be saved through her childbearing, if they continue in faith, love<G0026>, and sanctification with sobriety.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   3,   1, 'This is a faithful saying: someone who seeks to be an overseer desires a good work.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   3,   2, 'So the overseer must be without reproach, the husband of one wife, temperate, sensible, modest, hospitable, good at teaching;');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   3,   5, '(for how could someone who doesn\'t know how to rule his own house take care of God\'s assembly?)');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   3,   6, 'Not a new convert, lest being puffed up he fall into the same condemnation as the devil.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   3,   8, 'Servants, in the same way, must be reverent, not double-tongued, not addicted to much wine, not greedy for money,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   3,  11, 'Their wives in the same way must be reverent, not slanderers, temperate, and faithful in all things.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   3,  15, 'but if I wait long, that you may know how men ought to behave themselves in God\'s house, which is the assembly of the living God, the pillar and ground of the truth.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   4,   2, 'through the hypocrisy of men who speak lies, branded in their own conscience as with a hot iron,');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   4,   8, 'For bodily exercise is useful a little, but godliness is useful in all things, having the promise of the present life, and of that which is to come.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   4,  12, 'Let no man despise your youth; but be an example to those who believe, in word, in your way of life, in love<G0026>, in spirit, in faith, and in purity.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   4,  16, 'Pay attention to yourself and to your teaching. Continue in these things, for in doing this you will save both yourself and those who hear you.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   5,   4, 'But if any widow has children or grandchildren, let them first learn to demonstrate their faith toward their own family and repay their parents, for this is acceptable in the sight of God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   5,   5, 'Now she who is a widow indeed and desolate, has her hope set on God, and continues in petitions and prayers night and day.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   5,  10, 'being approved by good actions, if she has brought up children, if she has been hospitable to strangers, if she has washed the saints\' feet, if she has relieved the afflicted, and if she has diligently followed every good work.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   5,  11, 'But refuse younger widows, for when they have grown wanton against the AnointedOne<G5547>, they desire to marry,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   5,  14, 'So I desire that the younger widows marry, bear children, rule the household, and give no occasion to the adversary for insulting.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   5,  15, 'For already some have turned away following Satan.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   5,  16, 'If any man or woman who believes has widows, let them relieve them, and don\'t let the assembly be burdened, that it might relieve those who are widows indeed.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   5,  22, 'Don\'t lay hands hastily on anyone. Don\'t be a participant in other people\'s sins. Keep yourself pure.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   5,  25, 'In the same way also there are good actions that are obvious, and those that are otherwise can\'t be hidden.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,   1, 'Let as many as are bondservants under the yoke count their own masters<G1203> worthy of all honor, that the name of God and the doctrine not be blasphemed.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,   2, 'Those who have believing masters<G1203>, let them not despise them, because they are brothers, but rather let them serve them, because those who partake of the benefit are believing and dear-ones<G0027>. Teach and exhort these things.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  10, 'For the love of money is a root of all kinds of evil. Some have been led astray from the faith in their greed, and have pierced themselves through with many sorrows.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  11, 'But you, man of God, flee these things, and follow after righteousness, godliness, faith, love<G0026>, perseverance, and gentleness.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  12, 'Fight the good fight of faith. Take hold of the eternal life to which you were called, and you confessed the good confession in the sight of many witnesses.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  14, 'that you keep the commandment without spot, blameless, until the appearing of our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  15, 'which in its own times he will show, who is the blessed and only Ruler, the King of kings, and Lord<G2962> of lords<G2961>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  16, 'He alone has immortality, dwelling in unapproachable light, whom no man has seen, nor can see: to whom be honor and eternal power. Amen.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  17, 'Charge those who are rich in this present world not to be proud, nor have their hope set on the uncertainty of riches, but on the living God, who richly provides us with everything to enjoy;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  18, 'that they do good, that they be rich in good actions, that they be ready to distribute, generous;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  20, 'Timothy, guard that which is committed to you, turning away from the empty chatter and oppositions of what is falsely called knowledge,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1TI',   6,  21, 'which some profess, and thus have wandered from the faith. Grace be with you. Amen.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   1,   2, 'to Timothy, my dear<G0027> child: Grace, mercy, and peace, from God the Father and AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus our Lord<G2962>.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   1,   5, 'having been reminded of the sincere faith that is in you, which lived first in your grandmother Lois, and your mother Eunice, and, I am persuaded, in you also.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   1,   7, 'For God didn\'t give us a spirit of fear, but of power, love<G0026>, and soundness-of-mind<G4995>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   1,   8, 'So don\'t be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord<G2962>, nor of me his prisoner; but endure hardship for the Good News according to the power of God,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   1,   9, 'who saved us and called us with a holy calling, not according to our actions, but according to his own purpose and grace, which was given to us in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus before times eternal,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   1,  11, 'For this I was appointed as a preacher, an apostle, and a teacher of the Gentiles.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   1,  13, 'Hold the pattern of sound words which you have heard from me, in faith and love<G0026> which is in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   1,  15, 'This you know, that all who are in Asia turned away from me, of whom are Phygelus and Hermogenes.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   1,  17, 'but when he was in Rome, he sought me diligently and found me');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,   1, 'So you, my child, be strengthened in the grace that is in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,   2, 'The things which you have heard from me among many witnesses, present them to faithful men, who will be able to teach others also.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,   3, 'So, you must endure hardship as a good soldier of AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,   6, 'The farmer who labors must be the first to get a share of the crops.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,  10, 'So I endure all things for the chosen ones\' sake, that they also may obtain the salvation which is in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus with eternal glory.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,  11, 'This saying is trustworthy: \"For if we died with him, we will also live with him.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,  16, 'But shun empty chatter, for it will go further in ungodliness,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,  17, 'and those words will consume like gangrene, of whom is Hymenaeus and Philetus:');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,  21, 'So if anyone purges himself from these, he will be a vessel for honor, sanctified, and suitable for the master<G1203>\'s use, prepared for every good work.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,  22, 'Flee from youthful lusts; but pursue righteousness, faith, love<G0026>, and peace with those who call on the Lord<G2962> out of a pure heart.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   2,  24, 'The Lord<G2962>\'s servant must not quarrel, but be gentle toward all, able to teach, patient,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   3,   1, 'But know this: that in the last days, grievous times will come.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   3,   3, 'without natural affection, unforgiving, slanderers, without self-control, fierce, not lovers of good,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   3,   6, 'For some of these are people who creep into houses and take captive gullible women loaded down with sins, led away by various lusts,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   3,   8, 'Even as Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so these also oppose the truth, men corrupted in mind, who concerning the faith are rejected.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   3,  10, 'But you followed my teaching, conduct, purpose, faith, patience, love<G0026>, steadfastness,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   3,  11, 'persecutions, and sufferings: those things that happened to me at Antioch, Iconium, and Lystra. I endured those persecutions. The Lord<G2962> delivered me out of them all.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   3,  15, 'From infancy you have known the holy Scriptures, which are able to make you wise for salvation through faith which is in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   3,  16, 'All Scripture is Godbreathed<G2315> and useful; for teaching, for reproof, for correction, and for instruction in righteousness,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   3,  17, 'that each person who belongs to God may be complete, thoroughly equipped for every good work.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   4,   2, 'preach the word; be urgent in season and out of season; reprove, rebuke, and exhort with all patience and teaching.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   4,   4, 'and will turn away their ears from the truth, and turn away to fables.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   4,   8, 'From now on, the crown of righteousness is stored up for me, which the Lord<G2962>, the righteous judge, will give to me on that day; and not to me only, but also to all those who have loved<G0025> his appearing.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   4,  10, 'for Demas left<G1459> me, having loved<G0025> this present world, and went to Thessalonica; Crescens to Galatia, and Titus to Dalmatia.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   4,  14, 'Alexander, the coppersmith, did much evil to me. The Lord<G2962> will repay him according to his actions,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   4,  16, 'At my first defense, no one came to help me, but all left<G1459> me. May it not be held against them.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   4,  17, 'But the Lord<G2962> stood by me and strengthened me, that through me the message might be fully proclaimed, and that all the Gentiles might hear. So I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2TI',   4,  18, 'And the Lord<G2962> will deliver me from every evil work, and will preserve me for his heavenly Kingdom. To him be the glory forever and ever. Amen.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   1,   5, 'I left you in Crete for this reason, that you would set in order the things that were lacking and appoint elders in every city, as I directed you;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   1,   7, 'For the overseer must be blameless, as God\'s steward, not self-pleasing, not easily angered, not given to wine, not violent, not greedy for dishonest gain;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   1,   8, 'but given to hospitality, a lover of good, sober minded, fair, holy, self-controlled,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   1,  11, 'whose mouths must be stopped: men who overthrow whole houses, teaching things which they ought not, for dishonest gain\'s sake.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   1,  16, 'They profess that they know God, but by their actions they deny him, being abominable, disobedient, and unfit for any good work.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,   2, 'that older men should be temperate, sensible, sober minded, sound in faith, in love<G0026>, and in perseverance:');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,   3, 'and that older women likewise be reverent in behavior, not slanderers nor enslaved to much wine, teachers of that which is good,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,   4, 'that they may train the young wives to love their husbands, to love their children,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,   6, 'Likewise, exhort the young men to be sober minded.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,   7, 'In all things show yourself an example of good actions. In your teaching, show integrity, seriousness, incorruptibility,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,   8, 'and soundness of speech that can\'t be condemned, that he who opposes you may be ashamed having no evil thing to say about us.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,   9, 'Exhort servants to be in subjection to their own masters<G1203> and to be well-pleasing in all things, not contradicting,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,  10, 'not stealing, but showing all good fidelity, that they may adorn the doctrine of God, our Savior, in all things.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,  12, 'instructing us to the intent that, denying ungodliness and worldly lusts, we would lead sober, righteous, and godly lives in this present age;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,  13, 'looking for the blessed hope and appearing of the glory of our great God and Savior, Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,  14, 'who gave himself for us, that he might redeem us from all iniquity, and purify for himself a people for his own possession, zealous for good actions.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   2,  15, 'Say these things and exhort and reprove with all authority. Let none despise you.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   3,   4, 'But when the kindness of God our Savior and his love toward mankind appeared,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   3,   5, 'not by actions of righteousness which we did ourselves, but according to his mercy, he saved us through the washing of regeneration and renewing by the Holy Spirit,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   3,   8, 'This saying is faithful, and concerning these things I desire that you affirm confidently, so that those who have believed God may be careful to maintain good actions. These things are good and useful to men;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   3,  10, 'Avoid a factious man after a first and second warning,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   3,  11, 'knowing that such a one is perverted and sins, being self-condemned.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   3,  14, 'Let our people also learn to maintain good actions for necessary uses, that they may not be unfruitful.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('TIT',   3,  15, 'All who are with me greet you. Greet those who love us in faith. Grace be with you all. Amen.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,   1, 'Paul, a prisoner of AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus, and Timothy our brother, to Philemon, our dear<G0027> fellow worker,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,   2, 'and our sister Apphia, and Archippus our fellow soldier, and to the assembly in your house:');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,   5, 'hearing of your love<G0026> and of the faith which you have toward the Lord<G2962> Jesus and toward all the saints;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,   6, 'that the fellowship of your faith may become effective in the knowledge of every good thing which is in us in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,   7, 'For we have much joy and comfort in your love<G0026>, because the hearts of the saints have been refreshed through you, brother.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,   8, 'So, though I have all boldness in the AnointedOne<G5547> to command you that which is appropriate,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,   9, 'yet for love<G0026>\'s sake I rather beg, being such a one as Paul the old man and a prisoner for Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,  10, 'I beg you for my child, Onesimus, whom I have become the father of in my chains,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,  12, 'I am sending him back. Therefore receive him who is my very heart,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,  15, 'So perhaps he was separated from you for a while, that you would have him forever,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,  16, 'no longer as a slave, but more than a slave, a dear<G0027> brother, especially to me, but how much rather to you, both in the flesh and in the Lord<G2962>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,  17, 'If you count me a partner, receive him as you would receive me;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('PHM',   1,  18, 'and if he wrongs you at all or owes you anything, put that on my account.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   1,   3, 'His Son is the radiance of his glory, the very image of his substance, upholding all things by the word of his power. Once he had made purification for our sins he sat down on the right hand of the Majesty on high;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   1,   4, 'having become as much better than the angels as the name he has inherited is more excellent than theirs.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   1,   6, 'Again, when he brings the firstborn into the world he says, \"Let all the angels of God worship him.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   1,   7, 'Of the angels he says, \"He makes his angels winds, and his servants a flame of fire.\"');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   1,   9, 'You have loved<G0025> righteousness and hated iniquity; so God, your God, has anointed you with the oil of gladness above your fellows.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   1,  10, 'And, \"You, Lord<G2962>, in the beginning, laid the foundation of the earth; the heavens are the work of your hands.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   1,  12, 'You will roll them up like a mantle and they will be changed. But you are the same; your years won\'t fail.\"');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   2,   1, 'So we ought to pay greater attention to the things that were heard, lest perhaps we drift away.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   2,   2, 'For if the word spoken through angels proved steadfast, and every transgression and disobedience received a just penalty,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   2,   3, 'how will we escape if we neglect so great a salvation - which at the first having been spoken through the Lord<G2962>, was confirmed to us by those who heard;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   2,   4, 'God also testifying with them, both by signs and wonders, by various acts of power and by gifts of the Holy Spirit, according to his own will?');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   2,   7, 'You made him a little lower than the angels. You crowned him with glory and honor. [TR adds \"and set him over the actions of your hands\"]');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   2,  17, 'So he was obligated in all things to be made like his brothers, that he might become a merciful and faithful high priest in things pertaining to God, to make atonement for the sins of the people.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,   1, 'So, holy brothers, partakers of a heavenly calling, consider the Apostle and High Priest of our confession: Jesus,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,   2, 'who was faithful to him who appointed him, as also Moses was in all his house.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,   3, 'For he has been counted worthy of more glory than Moses, because he who built the house has more honor than the house.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,   6, 'but the AnointedOne<G5547> is faithful as a Son over his house. We are his house, if we hold fast our confidence and the glorying of our hope firm to the end.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,   7, 'So, even as the Holy Spirit says, \"Today if you will hear his voice,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,   8, 'don\'t harden your hearts, as in the rebellion, as in the day of the trial in the wilderness,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,   9, 'where your fathers tested me and tried me, and saw my actions for forty years.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,  10, 'So I was displeased with that generation, and said, \'They always err in their heart, but they didn\'t know my ways;\'');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,  12, 'Beware, brothers, lest perhaps there might be in any one of you an evil heart of unbelief, in falling away from the living God;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,  13, 'but exhort one another day by day, so long as it is called \"today\", lest any one of you be hardened by the deceitfulness of sin.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,  14, 'For we have become partakers of the AnointedOne<G5547>, if we hold on to the beginning of our confidence firm to the end:');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,  16, 'For who, when they heard, rebelled? Weren\'t all those who came out of Egypt led by Moses?');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   3,  19, 'We see that they weren\'t able to enter in because of unbelief.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,   1, 'So let\'s fear, lest perhaps anyone of you should seem to have come short of a promise of entering into his rest.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,   3, 'For we who have believed do enter into that rest, even as he has said, \"As I swore in my wrath, they will not enter into my rest;\" although the actions were finished from the foundation of the world.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,   4, 'For he has said this somewhere about the seventh day, \"God rested on the seventh day from all his work;\"');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,   6, 'So, seeing it remains that some should enter into it, and they to whom the good news was preached before failed to enter in because of disobedience,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,  10, 'For he who has entered into his rest has himself also rested from his work, as God did from his.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,  11, 'So let\'s give diligence to enter into that rest, lest anyone fall after the same example of disobedience.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,  12, 'For the word of God is living and active, and sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing even to the dividing of soul and spirit, of both joints and marrow, and is able to discern the thoughts and intentions of the heart.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,  13, 'There is no creature that is hidden from his sight, but all things are naked and laid open before the eyes of him to whom we must give an account.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,  14, 'Having then a great high priest who has passed through the heavens, Jesus, the Son of God, let\'s hold tightly to our confession.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   4,  16, 'So let\'s draw near with boldness to the throne of grace, that we may receive mercy and may find grace for help in time of need.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   5,   5, 'So also the AnointedOne<G5547> didn\'t glorify himself to be made a high priest, but it was he who said to him, \"You are my Son. Today I have become your father.\"');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   5,  12, 'For although by this time you should be teachers, you again need to have someone teach you the rudiments of the first principles of the revelations of God. You have come to need milk, and not solid food.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   6,   1, 'So leaving the teaching of the first principles of the AnointedOne<G5547>, let\'s press on to perfection - not laying again a foundation of repentance from dead actions, of faith toward God,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   6,   5, 'and tasted the good word of God and the powers of the age to come,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   6,   7, 'For the land which has drunk the rain that comes often on it and produces a crop suitable for them for whose sake it is also tilled, receives blessing from God;');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   6,  10, 'For God is not unrighteous, so as to forget your work and the labor of love<G0026> which you showed toward his name, in that you served the saints, and still do serve them.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   6,  12, 'that you won\'t be sluggish, but imitators of those who through faith and perseverance inherited the promises.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   6,  13, 'For when God made a promise to Abraham, since he could swear by no one greater, he swore by himself,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   6,  17, 'In this way God, being determined to show more abundantly to the heirs of the promise the immutability of his counsel, interposed with an oath,');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   7,   2, 'to whom also Abraham divided a tenth part of all (being first, by interpretation, \"king of righteousness\", and then also \"king of Salem\", which means \"king of peace\",');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   7,   4, 'Now consider how great this man was, to whom even Abraham, the patriarch, gave a tenth out of the best plunder.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   7,  11, 'Now if perfection was through the Levitical priesthood (for under it the people have received the law), what further need was there for another priest to arise after the order of Melchizedek, and not be called after the order of Aaron?');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   7,  25, 'So he is also able to save to the uttermost those who draw near to God through him, seeing that he lives forever to make intercession for them.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   8,   2, 'a servant of the sanctuary and of the true tabernacle, which the Lord<G2962> pitched, not man.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   8,   3, 'For every high priest is appointed to offer both gifts and sacrifices. So it is necessary that this high priest also have something to offer.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   8,   4, 'For if he were on earth, he would not be a priest at all, seeing there are priests who offer the gifts according to the law,');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   8,  12, 'For I will be merciful to their unrighteousness. I will remember their sins and lawless actions no more.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   8,  13, 'In that he says, \"A new covenant\", he has made the first old. But that which is becoming old and grows aged is near to vanishing away.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,   1, 'Now indeed even the first covenant had ordinances of divine service and an earthly sanctuary.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,   7, 'but into the second the high priest alone, once a year not without blood, which he offers for himself, and for the errors of the people.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,   8, 'The Holy Spirit is indicating this, that the way into the Holy Place wasn\'t yet revealed while the first tabernacle was still standing.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,   9, 'This is a symbol of the present age, where gifts and sacrifices are offered that are incapable, concerning the conscience, of making the worshiper perfect,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,  11, 'But the AnointedOne<G5547> having come as a high priest of the coming good things, through the greater and more perfect tabernacle, not made with hands, that is to say, not of this creation,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,  13, 'For if the blood of goats and bulls, and the ashes of a heifer sprinkling those who have been defiled, sanctify to the cleanness of the flesh,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,  14, 'how much more will the blood of the AnointedOne<G5547>, who through the eternal Spirit offered himself without defect to God, cleanse your conscience from dead actions to serve the living God?');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,  23, 'So it was necessary that the copies of the things in the heavens should be cleansed with these, but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,  24, 'For the AnointedOne<G5547> hasn\'t entered into holy places made with hands, which are representations of the true, but into heaven itself, now to appear in the presence of God for us;');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',   9,  28, 'so the AnointedOne<G5547> also, having been offered once to bear the sins of many, will appear a second time, without sin, to those who are eagerly waiting for him for salvation.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  10,   2, 'Or else wouldn\'t they have ceased to be offered, because the worshipers, having been once cleansed, would have had no more consciousness of sins?');
-
-
