-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,   9, 'By faith, he lived as an alien in the land of promise, as in a land not his own, dwelling in tents with Isaac and Jacob, the heirs with him of the same promise.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  16, 'But now they desire a better country, that is, a heavenly one. So God is not ashamed of them, to be called their God, for he has prepared a city for them.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  17, 'By faith, Abraham, being tested, offered up Isaac. Yes, he who had gladly received the promises was offering up his one and only son,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  18, 'to whom it was said, \"Your offspring will be accounted as from Isaac,\"');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  22, 'By faith, Joseph, when his end was near, made mention of the departure of the children of Israel, and gave instructions concerning his bones.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  25, 'choosing rather to share ill treatment with God\'s people than to enjoy the pleasures of sin for a time,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  26, 'considering the reproach of the AnointedOne<G5547> greater riches than the treasures of Egypt; for he looked to the reward.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  31, 'By faith, Rahab the prostitute didn\'t perish with those who were disobedient, having received the spies in peace.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  32, 'What more shall I say? For the time would fail me if I told of Gideon, Barak, Samson, Jephthah, David, Samuel, and the prophets,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  33, 'who through faith subdued kingdoms, worked out righteousness, obtained promises, stopped the mouths of lions,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  37, 'They were stoned. They were sawn apart. They were tempted. They were slain with the sword. They went around in sheep skins and in goat skins; being destitute, afflicted, ill-treated;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  11,  38, 'of whom the world was not worthy, wandering in deserts, mountains, caves, and the holes of the earth.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,   1, 'So let us also, seeing we are surrounded by so great a cloud of witnesses, lay aside every weight and the sin which so easily entangles us, and let\'s run with perseverance the race that is set before us,');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,   6, 'for whom the Lord<G2962> loves<G0025>, he disciplines, and chastises every son whom he receives.\"');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,   8, 'But if you are without discipline, of which all have been made partakers, then you are illegitimate, and not children.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  11, 'All chastening seems for the present to be not joyous but grievous; yet afterward it yields the peaceful fruit of righteousness to those who have been trained by it.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  12, 'So lift up the hands that hang down and the feeble knees,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  13, 'and make straight paths for your feet, so what is lame may not be dislocated, but rather be healed.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  20, 'for they could not stand that which was commanded, \"If even an animal touches the mountain, it shall be stoned.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  21, 'So fearful was the appearance that Moses said \"I am terrified and trembling.\"');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  23, 'to the festal gathering and assembly of the firstborn who are enrolled in heaven, to God the Judge of all, to the spirits of just men made perfect,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  25, 'See that you don\'t refuse him who speaks. For if they didn\'t escape when they refused him who warned on the Earth, how much more will we not escape who turn away from him who warns from heaven?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  26, 'His voice shook the earth then, but now he has promised, saying, \"Yet once more I will shake not only the earth, but also the heavens.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  27, 'This phrase, \"Yet once more\" signifies the removing of those things that are shaken, as of things that have been made, that those things which are not shaken may remain.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  12,  28, 'So, receiving a Kingdom that can\'t be shaken, let us have grace, through which we serve God acceptably, with reverence and awe,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  13,   1, 'Let brotherly love continue.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  13,   3, 'Remember those who are in bonds, as bound with them, and those who are ill-treated, since you are also in the body.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  13,   4, 'Let marriage be held in honor among all, and let the bed be undefiled; but God will judge the sexually immoral and adulterers.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  13,   5, 'Be free from the love of money, content with such things as you have, for he has said, \"I will in no way leave you, neither will I in any way forsake<G1459> you.\"');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  13,  11, 'For the bodies of those animals, whose blood is brought into the holy place by the high priest as an offering for sin, are burned outside the camp.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  13,  13, 'So let\'s go out to him outside of the camp, bearing his reproach.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  13,  15, 'Through him, then, let\'s offer up a sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of lips which proclaim allegiance to his name.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('HEB',  13,  22, 'But I exhort you, brothers, endure the word of exhortation; for I have written to you in few words.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,   5, 'But if any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask God, who gives to all liberally and without reproach, and it will be given to him.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,   7, 'For that man shouldn\'t think that he will receive anything from the Lord<G2962>.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,  11, 'For the sun rises with the scorching wind and withers the grass, and the flower in it falls, and the beauty of its appearance perishes. So the rich man will also fade away in his pursuits.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,  14, 'But each one is tempted when he is drawn away by his own lust and enticed.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,  15, 'Then the lust, when it has conceived, produces sin; and the sin, when it is full grown, brings death.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,  16, 'Don\'t be deceived, my dear<G0027> brothers.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,  18, 'Of his own will he gave birth to us by the word of truth, that we should be a kind of first fruits of his creatures.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,  19, 'So, then, my dear<G0027> brothers, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, and slow to anger;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,  21, 'So, putting away all filthiness and overflowing of wickedness, receive with humility the implanted word, which is able to save your souls.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,  25, 'But he who looks into the perfect law of freedom and continues, not being a hearer who forgets, but a doer of the work, this man will be blessed in what he does.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   1,  26, 'If anyone among you thinks himself to be religious while he doesn\'t control his tongue, but deceives his heart, this man\'s religion is worthless.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,   2, 'For if a man with a gold ring, in fine clothing, comes into your synagogue, and a poor man in filthy clothing also comes in,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,   3, 'and you pay special attention to the one who wears the fine clothing and say, \"Sit here in a good place;\" and you tell the poor man, \"Stand there,\" or \"Sit by my footstool;\"');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,   5, 'Listen, my dear<G0027> brothers. Didn\'t God choose those who are poor in this world to be rich in faith, and heirs of the Kingdom which he promised to those who love<G0025> him?');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,   8, 'However, if you fulfill the royal law according to the Scripture, \"You shall love<G0025> your neighbor as yourself,\" you do well.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  11, 'For he who said, \"Do not commit adultery,\" also said, \"Do not commit murder.\" Now if you do not commit adultery, but do murder, you have still become a transgressor of the law.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  12, 'So speak and act as men who are to be judged by a law of freedom.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  14, 'What good is it, my brothers, if a man says he has faith, but has no actions? Can faith save him?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  15, 'If a brother or sister is naked and in lack of daily food,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  16, 'and one of you tells them, \"Go in peace, be warmed and filled;\" but didn\'t give them the things the body needs, what good is it?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  17, 'Even so faith, if it has no actions, is dead in itself.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  18, 'Yes, a man will say, \"You have faith, and I have actions.\" Show me your faith without actions, and I will show you my faith by my actions.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  20, 'But do you want to know, vain man, that faith apart from actions is dead?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  21, 'Wasn\'t Abraham our father justified by actions, in that he offered up Isaac his son on the altar?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  22, 'You see that faith worked with his actions, and by actions faith was perfected.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  23, 'So the Scripture was fulfilled which says, \"Abraham believed God, and it was accounted to him as righteousness,\" and he was called the friend of God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  24, 'You see then that by actions, a man is justified, and not only by faith.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  25, 'In the same way, wasn\'t Rahab the prostitute also justified by actions, in that she received the messengers and sent them out another way?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   2,  26, 'For as the body apart from the spirit is dead, even so faith apart from actions is dead.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   3,   2, 'For we all stumble in many things. Anyone who doesn\'t stumble in word is a perfect man, able to control the whole body as well.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   3,   7, 'For every kind of animal, bird, creeping thing, and sea creature, is tamed, and has been tamed by mankind;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   3,   8, 'but nobody can tame the tongue. It is a restless evil, full of deadly poison.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   3,   9, 'With it we bless our God and Father, and with it we curse men who are made in the image of God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   3,  10, 'Both blessing and cursing come out of the same mouth. My brothers, these things ought not to be so.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   3,  13, 'Who is wise and understanding among you? Let him show by his good conduct that his actions are done in gentleness of wisdom.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   4,   2, 'You lust, and don\'t have. You murder and covet, and can\'t obtain. You fight and make war. You don\'t have, because you don\'t ask.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   4,   3, 'You ask, and don\'t receive, because you ask with wrong motives, so that you may spend it on your pleasures.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   4,   4, 'You adulterers and adulteresses, don\'t you know that friendship with the world is hostility toward God? So whoever wants to be a friend of the world makes himself an enemy of God.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   4,   7, 'So be subject to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   4,  14, 'Whereas you don\'t know what your life will be like tomorrow. For what is your life? For you are a vapor that appears for a little time, and then vanishes away.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   4,  17, 'So to him who knows to do good and doesn\'t do it, to him it is sin.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,   3, 'Your gold and your silver are corroded, and their corrosion will be for a testimony against you and will eat your flesh like fire. You have laid up your treasure in the last days.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,   5, 'You have lived in luxury on the earth, and taken your pleasure. You have nourished your hearts as in a day of slaughter.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,   6, 'You have condemned and murdered the righteous one. He doesn\'t resist you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,   7, 'So be patient brothers until the coming of the Lord<G2962>. Behold, the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the earth, being patient over it, until it receives the early and late rain.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,  10, 'Take, brothers, for an example of suffering and of perseverance, the prophets who spoke in the name of the Lord<G2962>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,  11, 'Behold, we call them blessed who endured. You have heard of the perseverance of Job, and have seen the Lord<G2962> in the outcome, and how the Lord<G2962> is full of compassion and mercy.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,  12, 'But above all things, my brothers, don\'t swear- not by heaven, or by the earth, or by any other oath; but let your \"yes\" be \"yes\", and your \"no\", \"no\", so that you don\'t fall into hypocrisy.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,  18, 'He prayed again, and the sky gave rain, and the earth produced its fruit.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,  19, 'Brothers, if any among you wanders from the truth and someone turns him back,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JAM',   5,  20, 'let him know that he who turns a sinner from the error of his way will save a soul from death and will cover a multitude of sins.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,   3, 'Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, who according to his great mercy caused us to be born again to a living hope through the resurrection of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> from the dead,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,   4, 'to a permanent<G0862> and undefiled inheritance that doesn\'t fade away, reserved in Heaven for you,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,   6, 'Wherein you greatly rejoice, though now for a little while, if need be, you have been grieved in various trials,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,   7, 'that the proof of your faith, which is more precious than gold that perishes even though it is tested by fire, may be found to result in praise, glory, and honor at the revelation of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> -');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,   8, 'whom, not having known, you love<G0025>. In him, though now you don\'t see him, yet believing, you rejoice greatly with joy that is unspeakable and full of glory,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  10, 'Concerning this salvation, the prophets sought and searched diligently, prophesying of the grace that would come to you,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  11, 'searching for who or what kind of time the Spirit of the AnointedOne<G5547>, which was in them, pointed to, when he predicted the sufferings of the AnointedOne<G5547>, and the glories that would follow them.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  12, 'To them it was revealed, that they served not themselves, but you, in these things, which now have been announced to you through those who preached the Good News to you by the Holy Spirit sent out from heaven; which things angels desire to look into.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  13, 'So prepare your minds for action; be sober and set your hope fully on the grace that will be brought to you at the revelation of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> -');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  17, 'If you call on him as Father, who without respect of persons judges according to each man\'s work, pass the time of your living as foreigners here in reverent fear,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  18, 'knowing that you were, not with temporary<G5349> silver or gold, redeemed from the useless way of life handed down from your fathers,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  19, 'but with precious blood, as of a faultless and pure lamb, the blood of the AnointedOne<G5547>;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  20, 'who was foreknown indeed before the foundation of the world, but was revealed in this last age for your sake,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  22, 'Seeing you have purified your souls in your obedience to the truth through the Spirit in sincere brotherly affection, love<G0025> one another from the heart fervently,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   1,  23, 'having been born again, not of temporary<G5349> seed, but of permanent<G0862>, through the word of God, which lives and remains forever.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,   1, 'So putting away all wickedness, all deceit, hypocrisies, envies, and all evil speaking,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,   2, 'as newborn babies, long for the pure milk of the Word, that with it you may grow,');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,   6, 'Because it is contained in Scripture, \"Behold, I lay in Zion a chief cornerstone, chosen and precious: He who believes in him will not be disappointed.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,   7, 'So the honor is for you who believe, but for those who are disobedient, \"The stone which the builders rejected, has become the chief cornerstone,\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,   8, 'and, \"a stumbling stone and a rock of offense.\" For they stumble at the word, being disobedient, to which also they were appointed.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,   9, 'But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people for God\'s own possession, that you may proclaim the excellence of him who called you out of darkness into his marvelous light.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  10, 'In the past, you were not a people, but now are God\'s people, who had not obtained mercy, but now have obtained mercy.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  12, 'having good behavior among the nations, so in that of which they speak against you as evildoers, they may by your good actions, which they see, glorify God in the day of visitation.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  13, 'So subject yourselves to every ordinance of man for the Lord<G2962>\'s sake: whether to the king, as supreme;');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  17, 'Honor all men. Love<G0025> the brotherhood. Fear God. Honor the king.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  18, 'Servants, be in subjection to your masters<G1203> with all respect: not only to the good and gentle, but also to the wicked.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  21, 'For you were called to this, because the AnointedOne<G5547> also suffered for us, leaving you an example, that you should follow his steps,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  22, 'who didn\'t sin, \"neither was deceit found in his mouth.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  23, 'When he was cursed, he didn\'t curse back. When he suffered, he didn\'t threaten, but committed himself to him who judges righteously.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  24, 'He himself bore our sins in his body on the tree, that we, having died to sins, might live to righteousness. You were healed by his wounds.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   2,  25, 'For you were going astray like sheep; but now you have returned to the Shepherd and Overseer of your souls.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,   1, 'In the same way, wives, be in subjection to your own husbands; so that, even if any don\'t obey the Word, they may be won by the behavior of their wives without a word,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,   4, 'but in the hidden person of the heart, in the permanent<G0862> adornment of a gentle and quiet spirit, which is very precious in the sight of God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,   5, 'For this is how in the past, the holy women who hoped in God also adorned themselves, being in subjection to their own husbands.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,   6, 'as Sarah obeyed Abraham, calling him Lord<G2962>, whose children you now are, if you do well, and are not put in fear by any terror.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,   7, 'You husbands, in the same way, live with your wives according to knowledge, giving honor to the woman, as to the weaker vessel, as also being joint heirs of the grace of life, that your prayers may not be hindered.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,   8, 'Finally, all of you be like-minded, compassionate, loving as brothers, tenderhearted, courteous,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,   9, 'not rendering evil for evil, or insult for insult; but instead blessing, knowing that you were called to this, that you may inherit a blessing.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,  11, 'Let him turn away from evil and do good. Let him seek peace and pursue it.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,  13, 'Now who will harm you if you become imitators of that which is good?');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,  16, 'having a good conscience; that, while you are spoken against as evildoers, they may be disappointed who curse your good way of life in the AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,  18, 'Because the AnointedOne<G5547> also suffered for sins once, the righteous for the unrighteous, that he might bring you to God; being put to death in the flesh, but made alive in the spirit;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,  19, 'in whom he also went and preached to the spirits in prison,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   3,  21, 'This is a symbol of baptism, which now saves you - not the putting away of the filth of the flesh, but the answer of a good conscience toward God, through the resurrection of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,   1, 'Therefore, since AnointedOne<G5547> suffered for us in the flesh, arm yourselves also with the same mind; for he who has suffered in the flesh has ceased from sin,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,   4, 'They think it is strange that you don\'t run with them into the same excess of riot, blaspheming.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,   5, 'They will give account to him who is ready to judge the living and the dead.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,   6, 'For to this end the Good News was preached even to the dead, that they might be judged indeed as people according to the flesh, but live according to God in the spirit.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,   7, 'But the end of all things is near. So be of sound mind, self-controlled, and sober in prayer.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,   8, 'And above all things be earnest in your love<G0026> among yourselves, for love<G0026> covers a multitude of sins.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,  11, 'If anyone speaks, let it be as it were the very words of God. If anyone serves, let it be with the strength which God supplies, that in all things God may be glorified through Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, to whom belong the glory and the dominion forever and ever. Amen.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,  12, 'Dear-ones<G0027>, don\'t be astonished at the fiery trial which has come upon you to test you, as though a strange thing happened to you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,  13, 'But because you are partakers of the AnointedOne<G5547>\'s sufferings, rejoice that at the revelation of his glory you also may rejoice with exceeding joy.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,  14, 'If you are insulted for the name of the AnointedOne<G5547>, you are blessed; because the Spirit of glory and of God rests on you. On their part he is blasphemed, but on your part he is glorified.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,  16, 'But if one of you suffers for being a Christian<G5546>, let him not be ashamed; but let him glorify God in this matter.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   4,  19, 'So let them also who suffer according to the will of God in doing good entrust their souls to him, as to a faithful Creator.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   5,   1, 'Therefore I exhort the elders among you, as a fellow elder and a witness of the sufferings of the AnointedOne<G5547>, and who will also share in the glory that will be revealed:');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   5,   2, 'shepherd the flock of God which is among you, exercising the oversight, not under compulsion, but voluntarily, not for dishonest gain, but willingly;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   5,   3, 'not as domineers<G2634> of those entrusted to you, but making yourselves examples to the flock.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   5,   4, 'When the chief Shepherd is revealed, you will receive the crown of glory that does not fade away.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   5,   6, 'So humble yourselves under the mighty hand of God, that he may exalt you in due time,');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1PE',   5,  14, 'Greet one another with a kiss of love<G0026>. Peace be to all of you who are in AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus. Amen.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   1,   3, 'seeing that his divine power has granted to us all things that pertain to life and godliness, through the knowledge of him who called us by his own glory and virtue,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   1,   6, 'and in knowledge, self-control; and in self-control perseverance; and in perseverance godliness;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   1,   7, 'and in godliness brotherly affection; and in brotherly affection, love<G0026>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   1,   8, 'For if these things are yours and abound, they make you neither idle nor unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   1,  10, 'So, brothers, be more diligent to make your calling and election sure. For if you do these things, you will never stumble.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   1,  12, 'So I will not be negligent to remind you of these things, though you know them, and are established in the present truth.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   1,  13, 'I think it right, as long as I am in this tent, to stir you up by reminding you,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   1,  16, 'For we didn\'t follow cunningly devised fables when we made known to you the power and coming of our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, but we were eyewitnesses of his majesty.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   1,  17, 'For he received from God the Father honor and glory when the voice came to him from the Majestic Glory, \"This is my dear<G0027> Son, in whom I am well pleased.\"');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   2,   1, 'But false prophets also arose among the people, as false teachers will also be among you, who will secretly bring in destructive heresies, denying even the Master<G1203> who bought them, bringing on themselves swift destruction.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   2,   4, 'For if God didn\'t spare angels when they sinned, but cast them down to Tartarus, and committed them to pits of darkness to be reserved for judgment;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   2,   6, 'and turning the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah into ashes, condemned them to destruction, having made them an example to those who would live in an ungodly way;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   2,   8, 'for that righteous man dwelling among them was tormented in his righteous soul from day to day with seeing and hearing lawless actions):');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   2,   9, 'the Lord<G2962> knows how to deliver the godly out of temptation and to keep the unrighteous under punishment for the day of judgment,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   2,  10, 'but chiefly those who walk after the flesh in the lust of defilement and despise authority. Daring, self-willed, they are not afraid to speak evil of dignitaries;');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   2,  13, 'receiving the wages of unrighteousness; people who count it pleasure to revel in the daytime, spots and defects, reveling in their deceit while they feast with you;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   2,  15, 'forsaking the right way, they went astray, having followed the way of Balaam the son of Beor, who loved<G0025> the wages of wrongdoing;');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   2,  19, 'promising them liberty, while they themselves are slaves of corruption; for a man is brought into slavery by whoever overcomes him.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,   1, 'This is now, dear-ones<G0027>, the second letter that I have written to you; and in both of them I stir up your sincere mind by reminding you');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,   2, 'that you should remember the words which were spoken before by the holy prophets and the commandment of us, the apostles of the Lord<G2962> and Savior:');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,   3, 'knowing this first, that in the last days mockers will come, walking after their own lusts');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,   5, 'For this they willfully forget that there were heavens from of old, and an earth formed out of water and amid water by the word of God,');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,   6, 'by which means the world that existed then, being overflowed with water, perished.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,   7, 'But the heavens that exist now and the earth, by the same word have been stored up for fire, being reserved against the day of judgment and destruction of ungodly men.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,   9, 'The Lord<G2962> is not slow concerning his promise, as some count slowness; but is patient with us, not wishing that anyone should perish, but that all should come to repentance.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,  10, 'But the day of the Lord<G2962> will come as a thief in the night; in which the heavens will pass away with a great noise, and the elements will be dissolved with fervent heat, and the earth and the work that is in it will be burned up.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,  11, 'So, since all these things will be destroyed like this, what kind of people ought you to be in holy living and godliness,');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,  14, 'So, dear-ones<G0027>, seeing that you look for these things, be diligent to be found in peace, without defect and blameless in his sight.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,  15, 'Regard the patience of our Lord<G2962> as salvation; even as our dear<G0027> brother Paul also, according to the wisdom given to him, wrote to you;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2PE',   3,  17, 'So you, dear-ones<G0027>, knowing these things beforehand, beware, lest being carried away with the error of the wicked, you fall from your own steadfastness.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   1,   2, 'and the life was revealed, and we have seen, and testify, and declare to you the life, the eternal life, which was with the Father, and was revealed to us);');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   2,   5, 'But God\'s love<G0026> has most certainly been perfected in whoever keeps his word. This is how we know that we are in him:');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   2,   8, 'Again, I write a new commandment to you, which is true in him and in you; because the darkness is passing away and the true light already shines.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   2,   9, 'He who says he is in the light and hates his brother is in darkness even until now.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   2,  10, 'He who loves<G0025> his brother remains in the light, and there is no occasion for stumbling in him.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   2,  15, 'Don\'t love<G0025> the world or the things that are in the world. If anyone loves<G0025> the world, the Father\'s love<G0026> isn\'t in him.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   2,  23, 'Whoever denies the Son doesn\'t have the Father. He who confesses the Son has the Father also.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   2,  24, 'So, as for you, let what you heard from the beginning remain in you. If what you heard from the beginning remains in you, you also will remain in the Son, and in the Father.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   2,  29, 'If you know that he is righteous, you know that everyone who practices righteousness has been born of him.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,   1, 'See how great a love<G0026> the Father has given to us, that we should be called children of God! For this cause the world doesn\'t know us, because it didn\'t know him.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,   2, 'Dear-ones<G0027>, now we are children of God. It is not yet revealed what we will be; but we know that when he is revealed, we will be like him; for we will see him just as he is.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,   5, 'You know that he was revealed to take away our sins, and no sin is in him.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,   6, 'Whoever remains in him doesn\'t sin. Whoever sins hasn\'t seen him and doesn\'t know him.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,   8, 'He who sins is of the devil, for the devil has been sinning from the beginning. To this end the Son of God was revealed: that he might destroy the actions of the devil.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,   9, 'Whoever is born of God doesn\'t commit sin, because his seed remains in him; and he can\'t sin, because he is born of God.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,  12, 'unlike Cain, who was of the evil one, and killed his brother. Why did he kill him? Because his actions were evil, and his brother\'s righteous.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,  16, 'By this we know love<G0026>, because he laid down his life for us. And we ought to lay down our lives for the brothers.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,  17, 'But whoever has the world\'s goods and sees his brother in need, then closes his heart of compassion against him, how does God\'s love<G0026> remain in him?');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,  18, 'My little children, let\'s not love<G0025> in word or with the tongue only, but in deed and truth.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   3,  22, 'so whatever we ask, we receive from him, because we keep his commandments and do the things that are pleasing in his sight.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,   5, 'They are of the world; so they speak of the world, and the world hears them.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,   7, 'Dear-ones<G0027>, let\'s love<G0025> one another, for love<G0026> is of God; and everyone who loves<G0025> has been born of God, and knows God.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,   9, 'By this God\'s love<G0026> was revealed in us, that God has sent his one and only Son into the world that we might live through him.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,  10, 'In this is love<G0026>, not that we loved<G0025> God, but that he loved<G0025> us, and sent his Son as the atoning sacrifice for our sins.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,  11, 'Dear-ones<G0027>, if God loved<G0025> us in this way, we also ought to love<G0025> one another.');
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,  16, 'We know and have believed the love<G0026> which God has for us. God is love<G0026>, and he who remains in love<G0026> remains in God, and God remains in him.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,  17, 'In this, love<G0026> has been made perfect among us, that we may have boldness in the day of judgment, because as he is, even so are we in this world.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,  18, 'There is no fear in love<G0026>; but perfect love<G0026> casts out fear, because fear has punishment. He who fears is not made perfect in love<G0026>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,  19, 'We love<G0025> him, because he first loved<G0025> us.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   4,  21, 'This commandment we have from him, that he who loves<G0025> God should also love<G0025> his brother.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   5,   1, 'Whoever believes that Jesus is the AnointedOne<G5547> has been born of God. Whoever loves<G0025> the Father also loves<G0025> the child who is born of him.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   5,   3, 'For this is loving<G0026> God, that we keep his commandments. His commandments are not grievous.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   5,   7, '[*For there are three who testify:]');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   5,   8, '[*the Spirit, the water, and the blood; and the three agree as one.]');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   5,  14, 'This is the boldness which we have toward him, that if we ask anything according to his will, he listens to us.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('1JO',   5,  20, 'We know that the Son of God has come, and has given us an understanding, that we know him who is true, and we are in him who is true, in his Son Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>. This is the true God and eternal life.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2JO',   1,   1, 'The elder, to the chosen lady and her children, whom I love<G0025> in truth; and not only me, but also all those who know the truth;');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2JO',   1,   3, 'Grace, mercy, and peace will be with us, from God the Father, and from the Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, the Son of the Father, in truth and love<G0026>.');
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2JO',   1,   9, 'Whoever transgresses and doesn\'t remain in the teaching of the AnointedOne<G5547>, doesn\'t have God. He who remains in the teaching has both the Father and the Son.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('2JO',   1,  11, 'for he who welcomes him participates in his evil actions.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('3JO',   1,   1, 'The elder, to dear<G0027> Gaius whom I love<G0025> in truth.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('3JO',   1,   3, 'For I rejoiced greatly when brothers came and testified about your truth, even as you walk in truth.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('3JO',   1,   4, 'I have no greater joy than this: to hear about my children walking in truth.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('3JO',   1,   6, 'They have testified about your love<G0026> before the assembly. You will do well to send them forward on their journey in a way worthy of God,');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('3JO',   1,   8, 'So we ought to receive such as these, that we may be fellow workers for the truth.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('3JO',   1,  10, 'So if I come, I will call attention to his actions which he does, unjustly accusing us with wicked words. Not content with this, neither does he himself receive the brothers, and those who would, he forbids and throws out of the assembly.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('3JO',   1,  14, 'but I hope to see you soon. Then we will speak face to face. Peace be to you. The friends greet you. Greet the friends by name.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,   1, 'Jude, a servant of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, and brother of James, to those who are called loved<G0025>, sanctified by God the Father, and kept for Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>:');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,   2, 'May mercy, peace and love<G0026> be multiplied to you.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,   4, 'For there are certain men who crept in secretly, even those who were long ago written about for this condemnation: ungodly men, turning the grace of our God into indecency, and denying our only Master<G1203>, God, and Lord<G2962>, Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,   7, 'Even as Sodom and Gomorrah and the cities around them, having in the same way as these given themselves over to sexual immorality and gone after strange flesh, are shown as an example, suffering the punishment of eternal fire.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,  10, 'But these speak evil of whatever things they don\'t know. They are destroyed in these things that they understand naturally, like creatures without reason.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,  12, 'These are hidden rocky reefs in your love<G0026> feasts when they feast with you, shepherds who without fear feed themselves; clouds without water, carried along by winds; autumn trees without fruit, twice dead, plucked up by the roots;');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,  15, 'to execute judgment on all, and to convict all the ungodly of all their actions of ungodliness which they have done in an ungodly way, and of all the hard things which ungodly sinners have spoken against him.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,  16, 'These are murmurers and complainers, walking after their lusts and their mouth speaks proud things, showing respect of persons to gain advantage.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,  18, 'They said to you, \"In the last time there will be mockers, walking after their own ungodly lusts.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,  19, 'These are those who cause divisions and are sensual, not having the Spirit.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,  21, 'Keep yourselves in the love<G0026> of God, looking for the mercy of our Lord<G2962> Jesus AnointedOne<G5547> to eternal life.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('JDE',   1,  23, 'and some save, snatching them out of the fire with fear, hating even the clothing<G5509> stained by the flesh.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   1,   2, 'who testified to God\'s word and of the testimony of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, about everything that he saw.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   1,   4, 'John, to the seven assemblies that are in Asia: Grace to you and peace from God, who is and who was and who is to come; and from the seven Spirits who are before his throne;');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   1,   5, 'and from Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>, the faithful witness, the firstborn of the dead, and the ruler of the kings of the earth. To him who loves<G0025> us, and washed us from our sins by his blood;');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   1,   8, '\"I am the Alpha and the Omega,\" says the Lord<G2962> God, \"who is and who was and who is to come, the Almighty<G3841>.\"');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   1,   9, 'I John, your brother and partner with you in oppression, Kingdom, and perseverance in the AnointedOne<G5547> Jesus, was on the isle that is called Patmos because of God\'s Word and the testimony of Jesus AnointedOne<G5547>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   1,  10, 'I was in the Spirit on the Lord<G2960>\'s day, and I heard behind me a loud voice, like a trumpet');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   1,  19, 'So write the things which you have seen, and the things which are, and the things which will happen hereafter.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   1,  20, 'The mystery of the seven stars which you saw in my right hand, and the seven golden lampstands is this: The seven stars are the angels of the seven assemblies. The seven lampstands are seven assemblies.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,   2, '\"I know your actions, and your toil and perseverance, and that you can\'t tolerate evil men, and have tested those who call themselves apostles, and they are not, and found them false.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,   4, 'But I have this against you, that you left your first love<G0026>.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,   5, 'So remember where you have fallen from, and repent and do the first actions; or else I am coming to you swiftly, and will move your lampstand out of its place, unless you repent.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,   6, 'But this you have, that you hate the actions of the Nicolaitans, which I also hate.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,   7, 'He who has an ear, let him hear what the Spirit says to the assemblies. To him who overcomes I will give to eat from the tree of life, which is in the Paradise of my God.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,   9, '\"I know your actions, oppression, and your poverty (but you are rich), and the blasphemy of those who say they are Jews, and they are not, but are a synagogue of Satan.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,  13, '\"I know your actions and where you dwell, where Satan\'s throne is. You hold firmly to my name, and didn\'t deny my faith in the days of Antipas my witness, my faithful one, who was killed among you, where Satan dwells.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,  16, 'So repent, or else I am coming to you quickly, and I will make war against them with the sword of my mouth.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,  19, '\"I know your actions, your love<G0026>, faith, service, patient endurance, and that your last actions are more than the first.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,  22, 'Behold, I will throw her and those who commit adultery with her into a bed of great oppression, unless they repent of her actions.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,  23, 'I will kill her children with Death, and all the assemblies will know that I am he who searches the minds and hearts. I will give to each one of you according to your actions.');
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   2,  26, 'He who overcomes, and he who keeps my actions to the end, to him I will give authority over the nations.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,   1, '\"And to the angel of the assembly in Sardis write: \"He who has the seven Spirits of God, and the seven stars says these things: \"I know your actions, that you have a reputation of being alive, but you are dead.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,   2, 'Wake up and keep the things that remain, which you were about to throw away, for I have found no actions of yours perfected before my God.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,   3, 'So remember how you have received and heard. Keep it, and repent. So if you won\'t watch, I will come like a thief, and you won\'t know what hour I will come upon you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,   4, 'Nevertheless you have a few names in Sardis that didn\'t defile their garments. They will walk with me in white, for they are worthy.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,   8, '\"I know your actions (behold, I have set before you an open door, which no one can shut), that you have a little power, and kept my word, and didn\'t deny my name.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,   9, 'Behold, I give some of the synagogue of Satan, of those who say they are Jews, and they are not, but lie. Behold, I will make them to come and worship before your feet, and to know that I have loved<G0025> you.');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,  10, 'Because you kept my command to endure, I also will keep you from the hour of testing which is to come on the whole world, to test those who dwell on the earth.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,  12, 'He who overcomes, I will make him a pillar in the temple of my God, and he will go out from there no more. I will write on him the name of my God and the name of the city of my God, the new Jerusalem, which comes down out of heaven from my God, and my own new name.');
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,  14, '\"To the angel of the assembly in Laodicea write: \"The Amen, the Faithful and True Witness, the Beginning of God\'s creation, says these things:');
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,  15, '\"I know your actions, that you are neither cold nor hot. I wish you were cold or hot.');
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   3,  19, 'As many as I love, I reprove and chasten. So be zealous, and repent.');
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INSERT INTO `verses` (`bookCode`, `chapter`, `verseNumber`, `verseText`) VALUES ('REV',   4,   8, 'The four living creatures, each one of them having six wings, are full of eyes around and within. They have no rest day and night, saying, \"Holy, holy, holy is the Lord<G2962> God, the Almighty<G3841>, who was and who is and who is to come!\"');
-
